var book = {
	"name": "Leviticus",
	"numChapters": 27,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2747A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2747A\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called Moses and spoke to him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2747B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2747B\"></sup>from the tent of meeting, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel and say to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2748C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2748C\"></sup>When any one of you brings an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you shall bring your offering of livestock from the herd or from the flock.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“If his offering is a burnt offering from the herd, he shall offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2749D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2749D\"></sup>a male without blemish. He shall bring it to the entrance of the tent of meeting, that he may be accepted before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2750E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2750E\"></sup>He shall lay his hand on the head of the burnt offering, and it shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2750F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2750F\"></sup>accepted for him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2750G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2750G\"></sup>to make atonement for him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then he shall kill the bull before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and Aaron's sons the priests shall bring the blood <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2751H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2751H\"></sup>and throw the blood against the sides of the altar that is at the entrance of the tent of meeting.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then he shall flay the burnt offering and cut it into pieces,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and the sons of Aaron the priest shall put fire on the altar and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2753I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2753I\"></sup>arrange wood on the fire.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Aaron's sons the priests shall arrange the pieces, the head, and the fat, on the wood that is on the fire on the altar;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>but its entrails and its legs he shall wash with water. And the priest shall burn all of it on the altar, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2755J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2755J\"></sup>a burnt offering, a food offering with a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2755K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2755K\"></sup>pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“If his gift for a burnt offering is from the flock, from the sheep or goats, he shall bring a male without blemish,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2757L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2757L\"></sup>and he shall kill it on the north side of the altar before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and Aaron's sons the priests shall throw its blood against the sides of the altar.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he shall cut it into pieces, with its head and its fat, and the priest shall arrange them on the wood that is on the fire on the altar,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>but the entrails and the legs he shall wash with water. And the priest shall offer all of it and burn it on the altar; it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2759M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2759M\"></sup>a burnt offering, a food offering with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2759N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2759N\"></sup>a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“If his offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a burnt offering of birds, then he shall bring his offering of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2760O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2760O\"></sup>turtledoves or pigeons.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the priest shall bring it to the altar and wring off its head and burn it on the altar. Its blood shall be drained out on the side of the altar.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He shall remove its crop with its contents and cast it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2762P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2762P\"></sup>beside the altar on the east side, in the place for ashes.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He shall tear it open by its wings, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2763Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2763Q\"></sup>shall not sever it completely. And the priest shall burn it on the altar, on the wood that is on the fire. It is a burnt offering, a food offering with a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>“When anyone brings a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2764A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2764A\"></sup>grain offering as an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, his offering shall be of fine flour. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2764B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2764B\"></sup>He shall pour oil on it and put frankincense on it",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and bring it to Aaron's sons the priests. And he shall take from it a handful of the fine flour and oil, with all of its frankincense, and the priest shall burn this as its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2765C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2765C\"></sup>memorial portion on the altar, a food <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2765D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2765D\"></sup>offering with a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2766E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2766E\"></sup>rest of the grain offering shall be for Aaron and his sons; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2766F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2766F\"></sup>it is a most holy part of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s food offerings.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“When you bring a grain offering baked in the oven as an offering, it shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2767G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2767G\"></sup>unleavened loaves of fine flour mixed with oil or unleavened wafers smeared with oil.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And if your offering is a grain offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2768H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2768H\"></sup>baked on a griddle, it shall be of fine flour unleavened, mixed with oil.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You shall break it in pieces and pour oil on it; it is a grain offering.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And if your offering is a grain offering cooked in a pan, it shall be made of fine flour with oil.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And you shall bring the grain offering that is made of these things to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and when it is presented to the priest, he shall bring it to the altar.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the priest shall take from the grain offering its memorial portion and burn this on the altar, a food <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2772I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2772I\"></sup>offering with a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2772J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2772J\"></sup>pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2773K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2773K\"></sup>rest of the grain offering shall be for Aaron and his sons; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2773L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2773L\"></sup>it is a most holy part of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s food offerings.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“No grain offering that you bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall be made with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2774M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2774M\"></sup>leaven, for you shall burn no leaven nor any honey as a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2775N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2775N\"></sup>As an offering of firstfruits you may bring them to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but they shall not be offered on the altar for a pleasing aroma.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2776O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2776O\"></sup>shall season all your grain offerings with salt. You shall not let the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2776P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2776P\"></sup>salt of the covenant with your God be missing from your grain offering; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2776Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2776Q\"></sup>with all your offerings you shall offer salt.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“If you offer a grain offering of firstfruits to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you shall offer for the grain offering of your firstfruits fresh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2777R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2777R\"></sup>ears, roasted with fire, crushed new grain.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2778S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2778S\"></sup>you shall put oil on it and lay frankincense on it; it is a grain offering.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the priest shall burn as its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2779T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2779T\"></sup>memorial portion some of the crushed grain and some of the oil with all of its frankincense; it is a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>“If his offering is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2780A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2780A\"></sup>a sacrifice of peace offering, if he offers an animal from the herd, male or female, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2780B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2780B\"></sup>he shall offer it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2780C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2780C\"></sup>without blemish before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2781D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2781D\"></sup>he shall lay his hand on the head of his offering and kill it at the entrance of the tent of meeting, and Aaron's sons the priests shall throw the blood against the sides of the altar.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And from the sacrifice of the peace offering, as a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he shall offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2782E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2782E\"></sup>the fat covering the entrails and all the fat that is on the entrails,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2783F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2783F\"></sup>and the two kidneys with the fat that is on them at the loins, and the long lobe of the liver that he shall remove with the kidneys.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Aaron's sons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2784G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2784G\"></sup>shall burn it on the altar on top of the burnt offering, which is on the wood on the fire; it is a food offering with a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“If his offering for a sacrifice of peace offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is an animal from the flock, male or female, he shall offer it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2785H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2785H\"></sup>without blemish.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If he offers a lamb for his offering, then he shall offer it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>lay his hand on the head of his offering, and kill it in front of the tent of meeting; and Aaron's sons shall throw its blood against the sides of the altar.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then from the sacrifice of the peace offering he shall offer as a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> its fat; he shall remove the whole <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2788I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2788I\"></sup>fat tail, cut off close to the backbone, and the fat that covers the entrails and all the fat that is on the entrails",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and the two kidneys with the fat that is on them at the loins and the long lobe of the liver that he shall remove <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2789J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2789J\"></sup>with the kidneys.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the priest shall burn it on the altar as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2790K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2790K\"></sup>a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“If his offering is a goat, then he shall offer it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and lay his hand on its head and kill it in front of the tent of meeting, and the sons of Aaron shall throw its blood against the sides of the altar.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he shall offer from it, as his offering for a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the fat covering the entrails and all the fat that is on the entrails",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and the two kidneys with the fat that is on them at the loins and the long lobe of the liver that he shall remove <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2794L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2794L\"></sup>with the kidneys.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the priest shall burn them on the altar as a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2795M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2795M\"></sup>food offering with a pleasing aroma. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2795N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2795N\"></sup>All fat is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>It shall be a statute forever throughout your generations, in all your dwelling places, that you eat neither <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2796O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2796O\"></sup>fat nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2796P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2796P\"></sup>blood.”"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2798A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2798A\"></sup>If anyone sins unintentionally in any of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s commandments <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2798B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2798B\"></sup>about things not to be done, and does any one of them,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>if it is the anointed priest who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2799C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2799C\"></sup>sins, thus bringing guilt on the people, then he shall offer for the sin that he has committed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2799D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2799D\"></sup>a bull from the herd without blemish to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for a sin offering.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He shall bring the bull to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2800E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2800E\"></sup>entrance of the tent of meeting before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and lay his hand on the head of the bull and kill the bull before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the anointed priest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2801F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2801F\"></sup>shall take some of the blood of the bull and bring it into the tent of meeting,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and the priest shall dip his finger in the blood and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2802G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2802G\"></sup>sprinkle part of the blood seven times before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in front of the veil of the sanctuary.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the priest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2803H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2803H\"></sup>shall put some of the blood on the horns of the altar of fragrant incense before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that is in the tent of meeting, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2803I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2803I\"></sup>all the rest of the blood of the bull he shall pour out at the base of the altar of burnt offering that is at the entrance of the tent of meeting.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And all the fat of the bull of the sin offering he shall remove from it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2804J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2804J\"></sup>the fat that covers the entrails and all the fat that is on the entrails",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2805K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2805K\"></sup>and the two kidneys with the fat that is on them at the loins and the long lobe of the liver that he shall remove with the kidneys",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>(just as these are taken from the ox of the sacrifice of the peace offerings); and the priest shall burn them on the altar of burnt offering.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2807L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2807L\"></sup>the skin of the bull and all its flesh, with its head, its legs, its entrails, and its dung—",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>all the rest of the bull—he shall carry <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2808M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2808M\"></sup>outside the camp to a clean place, to the ash heap, and shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2808N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2808N\"></sup>burn it up on a fire of wood. On the ash heap it shall be burned up.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2809O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2809O\"></sup>“If the whole congregation of Israel sins unintentionally and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2809P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2809P\"></sup>the thing is hidden from the eyes of the assembly, and they do any one of the things that by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s commandments ought not to be done, and they realize their guilt,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2810Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2810Q\"></sup>when the sin which they have committed becomes known, the assembly shall offer a bull from the herd for a sin offering and bring it in front of the tent of meeting.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the elders of the congregation <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2811R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2811R\"></sup>shall lay their hands on the head of the bull before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the bull shall be killed before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2812S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2812S\"></sup>the anointed priest shall bring some of the blood of the bull into the tent of meeting,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and the priest shall dip his finger in the blood and sprinkle it seven times before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in front of the veil.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he shall put some of the blood on the horns of the altar that is in the tent of meeting before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the rest of the blood he shall pour out at the base of the altar of burnt offering that is at the entrance of the tent of meeting.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And all its fat he shall take from it and burn on the altar.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Thus shall he do with the bull. As he did <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2816T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2816T\"></sup>with the bull of the sin offering, so shall he do with this. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2816U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2816U\"></sup>And the priest shall make atonement for them, and they shall be forgiven.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And he shall carry the bull <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2817V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2817V\"></sup>outside the camp and burn it up as he burned the first bull; it is the sin offering for the assembly.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“When a leader sins, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2818W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2818W\"></sup>doing unintentionally any one of all the things that by the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God ought not to be done, and realizes his guilt,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2819X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2819X\"></sup>the sin which he has committed is made known to him, he shall bring as his offering a goat, a male without blemish,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2820Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2820Y\"></sup>shall lay his hand on the head of the goat and kill it in the place where they kill the burnt offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it is a sin offering.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2821Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2821Z\"></sup>Then the priest shall take some of the blood of the sin offering with his finger and put it on the horns of the altar of burnt offering and pour out the rest of its blood at the base of the altar of burnt offering.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And all its fat he shall burn on the altar, like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2822AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2822AA\"></sup>the fat of the sacrifice of peace offerings. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2822AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2822AB\"></sup>the priest shall make atonement for him for his sin, and he shall be forgiven.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“If <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2823AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2823AC\"></sup>anyone of the common people sins unintentionally in doing any one of the things that by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s commandments ought not to be done, and realizes his guilt,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2824AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2824AD\"></sup>or the sin which he has committed is made known to him, he shall bring for his offering a goat, a female without blemish, for his sin which he has committed.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2825AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2825AE\"></sup>And he shall lay his hand on the head of the sin offering and kill the sin offering in the place of burnt offering.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the priest shall take some of its blood with his finger and put it on the horns of the altar of burnt offering and pour out all the rest of its blood at the base of the altar.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2827AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2827AF\"></sup>all its fat he shall remove, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2827AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2827AG\"></sup>as the fat is removed from the peace offerings, and the priest shall burn it on the altar for a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2827AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2827AH\"></sup>pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2827AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2827AI\"></sup>And the priest shall make atonement for him, and he shall be forgiven.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“If he brings a lamb as his offering for a sin offering, he shall bring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2828AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2828AJ\"></sup>a female without blemish",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2829AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2829AK\"></sup>and lay his hand on the head of the sin offering and kill it for a sin offering in the place where they kill the burnt offering.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then the priest shall take some of the blood of the sin offering with his finger and put it on the horns of the altar of burnt offering and pour out all the rest of its blood at the base of the altar.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And all its fat he shall remove <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2831AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2831AL\"></sup>as the fat of the lamb is removed from the sacrifice of peace offerings, and the priest shall burn it on the altar, on top of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s food offerings. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2831AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2831AM\"></sup>And the priest shall make atonement for him for the sin which he has committed, and he shall be forgiven."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>“If anyone sins in that he hears a public <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2832A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2832A\"></sup>adjuration to testify, and though he is a witness, whether he has seen or come to know the matter, yet does not speak, he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2832B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2832B\"></sup>bear his iniquity;",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2833C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2833C\"></sup>if anyone touches an unclean thing, whether a carcass of an unclean wild animal or a carcass of unclean livestock or a carcass of unclean swarming things, and it is hidden from him and he has become unclean, and he realizes his guilt;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>or if he touches <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2834D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2834D\"></sup>human uncleanness, of whatever sort the uncleanness may be with which one becomes unclean, and it is hidden from him, when he comes to know it, and realizes his guilt;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>or if anyone utters with his lips a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2835E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2835E\"></sup>rash oath to do evil or to do good, any sort of rash oath that people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2835F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2835F\"></sup>swear, and it is hidden from him, when he comes to know it, and he realizes his guilt in any of these;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>when he realizes his guilt in any of these and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2836G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2836G\"></sup>confesses the sin he has committed,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>he shall bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as his compensation for the sin that he has committed, a female from the flock, a lamb or a goat, for a sin offering. And the priest shall make atonement for him for his sin.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2838H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2838H\"></sup>if he cannot afford a lamb, then he shall bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as his compensation for the sin that he has committed two <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2838I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2838I\"></sup>turtledoves or two pigeons, one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He shall bring them to the priest, who shall offer first the one for the sin offering. He shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2839J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2839J\"></sup>wring its head from its neck <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2839K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2839K\"></sup>but shall not sever it completely,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and he shall sprinkle some of the blood of the sin offering on the side of the altar, while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2840L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2840L\"></sup>the rest of the blood shall be drained out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2840M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2840M\"></sup>at the base of the altar; it is a sin offering.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then he shall offer the second for a burnt offering according to the rule. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2841N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2841N\"></sup>And the priest shall make atonement for him for the sin that he has committed, and he shall be forgiven.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“But if he cannot afford two turtledoves or two pigeons, then he shall bring as his offering for the sin that he has committed a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2842O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2842O\"></sup>tenth of an ephah of fine flour for a sin offering. He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2842P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2842P\"></sup>shall put no oil on it and shall put no frankincense on it, for it is a sin offering.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he shall bring it to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2843Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2843Q\"></sup>the priest, and the priest shall take a handful of it as its memorial portion and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2843R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2843R\"></sup>burn this on the altar, on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s food offerings; it is a sin offering.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2844S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2844S\"></sup>the priest shall make atonement for him for the sin which he has committed in any one of these things, and he shall be forgiven. And the remainder shall be for the priest, as in the grain offering.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2846T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2846T\"></sup>“If anyone commits a breach of faith and sins unintentionally in any of the holy things of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2846U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2846U\"></sup>he shall bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as his compensation, a ram without blemish out of the flock, valued in silver shekels, according to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2846V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2846V\"></sup>shekel of the sanctuary, for a guilt offering.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He shall also make restitution for what he has done amiss in the holy thing and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2847W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2847W\"></sup>shall add a fifth to it and give it to the priest. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2847X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2847X\"></sup>And the priest shall make atonement for him with the ram of the guilt offering, and he shall be forgiven.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2848Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2848Y\"></sup>“If anyone sins, doing any of the things that by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s commandments ought not to be done, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2848Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2848Z\"></sup>though he did not know it, then realizes his guilt, he shall bear his iniquity.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2849AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2849AA\"></sup>He shall bring to the priest a ram without blemish out of the flock, or its equivalent, for a guilt offering, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2849AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2849AB\"></sup>the priest shall make atonement for him for the mistake that he made unintentionally, and he shall be forgiven.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>It is a guilt offering; he has indeed incurred guilt before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span> The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“If anyone sins and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2852A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2852A\"></sup>commits a breach of faith against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2852B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2852B\"></sup>deceiving his neighbor in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2852C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2852C\"></sup>a matter of deposit or security, or through robbery, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2852D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2852D\"></sup>if he has oppressed his neighbor",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2853E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2853E\"></sup>has found something lost and lied about it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2853F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2853F\"></sup>swearing falsely—in any of all the things that people do and sin thereby—",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>if he has sinned and has realized his guilt and will restore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2854G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2854G\"></sup>what he took by robbery or what he got by oppression or the deposit that was committed to him or the lost thing that he found",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>or anything about which he has sworn falsely, he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2855H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2855H\"></sup>restore it in full and shall add a fifth to it, and give it to him to whom it belongs on the day he realizes his guilt.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he shall bring to the priest as his compensation to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2856I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2856I\"></sup>a ram without blemish out of the flock, or its equivalent, for a guilt offering.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2857J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2857J\"></sup>And the priest shall make atonement for him before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he shall be forgiven for any of the things that one may do and thereby become guilty.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup> The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Command Aaron and his sons, saying, This is the law of the burnt offering. The burnt offering shall be on the hearth on the altar all night until the morning, and the fire of the altar shall be kept burning on it.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2860K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2860K\"></sup>the priest shall put on his linen garment and put his linen undergarment on his body, and he shall take up the ashes to which the fire has reduced the burnt offering on the altar and put them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2860L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2860L\"></sup>beside the altar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2861M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2861M\"></sup>he shall take off his garments and put on other garments and carry the ashes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2861N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2861N\"></sup>outside the camp to a clean place.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The fire on the altar shall be kept burning on it; it shall not go out. The priest shall burn wood on it every morning, and he shall arrange the burnt offering on it and shall burn on it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2862O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2862O\"></sup>the fat of the peace offerings.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Fire shall be kept burning on the altar continually; it shall not go out.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“And this is the law of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2864P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2864P\"></sup>the grain offering. The sons of Aaron shall offer it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in front of the altar.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And one shall take from it a handful of the fine flour of the grain offering and its oil and all the frankincense that is on the grain offering and burn this as its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2865Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2865Q\"></sup>memorial portion on the altar, a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2866R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2866R\"></sup>the rest of it Aaron and his sons shall eat. It shall be eaten unleavened <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2866S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2866S\"></sup>in a holy place. In the court of the tent of meeting they shall eat it.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2867T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2867T\"></sup>It shall not be baked with leaven. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2867U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2867U\"></sup>I have given it as their portion of my food offerings. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2867V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2867V\"></sup>It is a thing most holy, like the sin offering and the guilt offering.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Every male among the children of Aaron may eat of it, as decreed forever throughout your generations, from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s food offerings. Whatever touches them shall become holy.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2870W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2870W\"></sup>“This is the offering that Aaron and his sons shall offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the day when he is anointed: a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2870X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2870X\"></sup>tenth of an ephah of fine flour as a regular grain offering, half of it in the morning and half in the evening.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>It shall be made with oil <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2871Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2871Y\"></sup>on a griddle. You shall bring it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2871Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2871Z\"></sup>well mixed, in baked pieces like a grain offering, and offer it for a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The priest from among Aaron's sons, who is anointed to succeed him, shall offer it to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as decreed forever. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2872AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2872AA\"></sup>The whole of it shall be burned.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Every grain offering of a priest shall be wholly burned. It shall not be eaten.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Speak to Aaron and his sons, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2875AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2875AB\"></sup>This is the law of the sin offering. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2875AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2875AC\"></sup>In the place where the burnt offering is killed shall the sin offering be killed before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2875AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2875AD\"></sup>it is most holy.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2876AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2876AE\"></sup>The priest who offers it for sin shall eat it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2876AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2876AF\"></sup>In a holy place it shall be eaten, in the court of the tent of meeting.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Whatever touches its flesh shall be holy, and when any of its blood is splashed on a garment, you shall wash that on which it was splashed in a holy place.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2878AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2878AG\"></sup>the earthenware vessel in which it is boiled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2878AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2878AH\"></sup>shall be broken. But if it is boiled in a bronze vessel, that shall be scoured and rinsed in water.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Every male among the priests may eat of it; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2879AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2879AI\"></sup>it is most holy.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2880AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2880AJ\"></sup>But no sin offering shall be eaten from which any blood is brought into the tent of meeting to make atonement in the Holy Place; it shall be burned up with fire."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2881A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2881A\"></sup>“This is the law of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2881B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2881B\"></sup>guilt offering. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2881C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2881C\"></sup>It is most holy.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2882D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2882D\"></sup>In the place where they kill the burnt offering they shall kill the guilt offering, and its blood shall be thrown against the sides of the altar.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2883E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2883E\"></sup>all its fat shall be offered, the fat tail, the fat that covers the entrails,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>the two kidneys with the fat that is on them at the loins, and the long lobe of the liver that he shall remove <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2884F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2884F\"></sup>with the kidneys.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The priest shall burn them on the altar as a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it is a guilt offering.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2886G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2886G\"></sup>Every male among the priests may eat of it. It shall be eaten in a holy place. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2886H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2886H\"></sup>It is most holy.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2887I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2887I\"></sup>guilt offering is just like the sin offering; there is one law for them. The priest who makes atonement with it shall have it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the priest who offers any man's burnt offering shall have for himself the skin of the burnt offering that he has offered.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2889J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2889J\"></sup>every grain offering baked <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2889K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2889K\"></sup>in the oven and all that is prepared <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2889L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2889L\"></sup>on a pan or a griddle shall belong to the priest who offers it.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And every grain offering, mixed with oil or dry, shall be shared equally among all the sons of Aaron.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“And this is the law of the sacrifice of peace offerings that one may offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>If he offers it for a thanksgiving, then he shall offer with the thanksgiving sacrifice <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2892M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2892M\"></sup>unleavened loaves mixed with oil, unleavened wafers smeared with oil, and loaves of fine flour <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2892N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2892N\"></sup>well mixed with oil.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2893O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2893O\"></sup>With the sacrifice of his peace offerings for thanksgiving he shall bring his offering with loaves of leavened bread.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And from it he shall offer one loaf from each offering, as a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2894P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2894P\"></sup>gift to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2894Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2894Q\"></sup>It shall belong to the priest who throws the blood of the peace offerings.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the flesh of the sacrifice of his peace offerings <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2895R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2895R\"></sup>for thanksgiving shall be eaten on the day of his offering. He shall not leave any of it until the morning.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2896S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2896S\"></sup>if the sacrifice of his offering is a vow offering or a freewill offering, it shall be eaten on the day that he offers his sacrifice, and on the next day what remains of it shall be eaten.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But what remains of the flesh of the sacrifice on the third day shall be burned up with fire.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>If any of the flesh of the sacrifice of his peace offering is eaten on the third day, he who offers it shall not be accepted, neither shall it be credited to him. It is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2898T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2898T\"></sup>tainted, and he who eats of it shall bear his iniquity.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Flesh that touches any unclean thing shall not be eaten. It shall be burned up with fire. All who are clean may eat flesh,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>but the person who eats of the flesh of the sacrifice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s peace offerings <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2900U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2900U\"></sup>while an uncleanness is on him, that person shall be cut off from his people.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And if anyone touches an unclean thing, whether <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2901V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2901V\"></sup>human uncleanness or an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2901W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2901W\"></sup>unclean beast or any <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2901X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2901X\"></sup>unclean detestable creature, and then eats some flesh from the sacrifice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s peace offerings, that person shall be cut off from his people.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2903Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2903Y\"></sup>You shall eat no fat, of ox or sheep or goat.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The fat of an animal <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2904Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2904Z\"></sup>that dies of itself and the fat of one that is torn by beasts may be put to any other use, but on no account shall you eat it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For every person who eats of the fat of an animal of which a food offering may be made to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall be cut off from his people.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2906AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2906AA\"></sup>you shall eat no blood whatever, whether of fowl or of animal, in any of your dwelling places.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Whoever eats any blood, that person shall be cut off from his people.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2909AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2909AB\"></sup>Whoever offers the sacrifice of his peace offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall bring his offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from the sacrifice of his peace offerings.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2910AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2910AC\"></sup>His own hands shall bring the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s food offerings. He shall bring the fat with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2910AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2910AD\"></sup>the breast, that the breast may be waved as a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2911AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2911AE\"></sup>The priest shall burn the fat on the altar, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2911AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2911AF\"></sup>the breast shall be for Aaron and his sons.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2912AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2912AG\"></sup>the right thigh you shall give to the priest as a contribution from the sacrifice of your peace offerings.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Whoever among the sons of Aaron offers the blood of the peace offerings and the fat shall have the right thigh for a portion.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>For the breast that is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2914AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2914AH\"></sup>waved and the thigh that is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2914AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2914AI\"></sup>contributed I have taken from the people of Israel, out of the sacrifices of their peace offerings, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2914AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2914AJ\"></sup>have given them to Aaron the priest and to his sons, as a perpetual due from the people of Israel.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>This is the portion of Aaron and of his sons from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s food offerings, from the day they were presented to serve as priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded this to be given them by the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2916AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2916AK\"></sup>from the day that he anointed them. It is a perpetual due throughout their generations.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>This is the law <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2917AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2917AL\"></sup>of the burnt offering, of the grain offering, of the sin offering, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2917AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2917AM\"></sup>of the guilt offering, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2917AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2917AN\"></sup>of the ordination offering, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2917AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2917AO\"></sup>of the peace offering,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses on Mount Sinai, on the day that he commanded the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2918AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2918AP\"></sup>to bring their offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in the wilderness of Sinai."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2919A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2919A\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Take Aaron and his sons with him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2920B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2920B\"></sup>the garments and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2920C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2920C\"></sup>the anointing oil and the bull of the sin offering and the two rams and the basket of unleavened bread.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And assemble all the congregation at the entrance of the tent of meeting.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Moses did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded him, and the congregation was assembled at the entrance of the tent of meeting.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Moses said to the congregation, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2923D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2923D\"></sup>“This is the thing that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded to be done.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Moses brought Aaron and his sons and washed them with water.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2925E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2925E\"></sup>the coat on him and tied the sash around his waist and clothed him with the robe and put the ephod on him and tied the skillfully woven band of the ephod around him, binding it to him with the band.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he placed the breastpiece on him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2926F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2926F\"></sup>in the breastpiece he put the Urim and the Thummim.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he set <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2927G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2927G\"></sup>the turban on his head, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2927H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2927H\"></sup>on the turban, in front, he set the golden plate, the holy crown, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2928I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2928I\"></sup>Then Moses took the anointing oil and anointed the tabernacle and all that was in it, and consecrated them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he sprinkled some of it on the altar seven times, and anointed the altar and all its utensils and the basin and its stand, to consecrate them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2930J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2930J\"></sup>he poured some of the anointing oil on Aaron's head and anointed him to consecrate him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Moses brought Aaron's sons and clothed them with coats and tied sashes around their waists and bound caps on them, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he brought <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2932K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2932K\"></sup>the bull of the sin offering, and Aaron and his sons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2932L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2932L\"></sup>laid their hands on the head of the bull of the sin offering.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he killed it, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2933M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2933M\"></sup>Moses took the blood, and with his finger put it on the horns of the altar around it and purified the altar and poured out the blood at the base of the altar and consecrated it to make atonement for it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2934N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2934N\"></sup>And he took all the fat that was on the entrails and the long lobe of the liver and the two kidneys with their fat, and Moses burned them on the altar.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2935O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2935O\"></sup>the bull and its skin and its flesh and its dung he burned up with fire outside the camp, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2936P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2936P\"></sup>Then he presented the ram of the burnt offering, and Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the head of the ram.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he killed it, and Moses threw the blood against the sides of the altar.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He cut the ram into pieces, and Moses burned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2938Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2938Q\"></sup>the head and the pieces and the fat.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He washed the entrails and the legs with water, and Moses burned the whole ram on the altar. It was a burnt offering with a pleasing aroma, a food offering for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2940R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2940R\"></sup>he presented the other ram, the ram of ordination, and Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the head of the ram.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And he killed it, and Moses took some of its blood and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2941S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2941S\"></sup>put it on the lobe of Aaron's right ear and on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then he presented Aaron's sons, and Moses put some of the blood on the lobes of their right ears and on the thumbs of their right hands and on the big toes of their right feet. And Moses threw the blood against the sides of the altar.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then he took the fat and the fat tail and all the fat that was on the entrails and the long lobe of the liver and the two kidneys with their fat and the right thigh,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and out of the basket of unleavened bread that was before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> he took one unleavened loaf and one loaf of bread with oil and one wafer and placed them on the pieces of fat and on the right thigh.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And he put all these in the hands of Aaron and in the hands of his sons and waved them as a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Moses took them from their hands and burned them on the altar with the burnt offering. This was an ordination offering with a pleasing aroma, a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Moses took the breast and waved it for a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. It was Moses' portion of the ram of ordination, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2948T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2948T\"></sup>Moses took some of the anointing oil and of the blood that was on the altar and sprinkled it on Aaron and his garments, and also on his sons and his sons' garments. So he consecrated Aaron and his garments, and his sons and his sons' garments with him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And Moses said to Aaron and his sons, “Boil the flesh at the entrance of the tent of meeting, and there eat it and the bread that is in the basket of ordination offerings, as I commanded, saying, ‘Aaron and his sons shall eat it.’",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And what remains of the flesh and the bread you shall burn up with fire.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And you shall not go outside the entrance of the tent of meeting for seven days, until the days of your ordination are completed, for it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2951U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2951U\"></sup>will take seven days to ordain you.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>As has been done today, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded to be done to make atonement for you.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>At the entrance of the tent of meeting you shall remain day and night for seven days, performing what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2953V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2953V\"></sup>charged, so that you do not die, for so I have been commanded.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And Aaron and his sons did all the things that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded by Moses."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2955A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2955A\"></sup>On the eighth day Moses called Aaron and his sons and the elders of Israel,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and he said to Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2956B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2956B\"></sup>“Take for yourself a bull calf for a sin offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2956C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2956C\"></sup>a ram for a burnt offering, both without blemish, and offer them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And say to the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2957D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2957D\"></sup>‘Take a male goat for a sin offering, and a calf and a lamb, both a year old without blemish, for a burnt offering,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and an ox and a ram for peace offerings, to sacrifice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2958E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2958E\"></sup>a grain offering mixed with oil, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2958F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2958F\"></sup>today the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will appear to you.’”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And they brought what Moses commanded in front of the tent of meeting, and all the congregation drew near and stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Moses said, “This is the thing that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded you to do, that the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may appear to you.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Moses said to Aaron, “Draw near to the altar and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2961G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2961G\"></sup>offer your sin offering and your burnt offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2961H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2961H\"></sup>make atonement for yourself and for the people, and bring the offering of the people and make atonement for them, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Aaron drew near to the altar and killed the calf of the sin offering, which was for himself.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2963I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2963I\"></sup>And the sons of Aaron presented the blood to him, and he dipped his finger in the blood and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2963J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2963J\"></sup>put it on the horns of the altar and poured out the blood at the base of the altar.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2964K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2964K\"></sup>But the fat and the kidneys and the long lobe of the liver from the sin offering he burned on the altar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2964L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2964L\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2965M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2965M\"></sup>The flesh and the skin he burned up with fire outside the camp.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he killed the burnt offering, and Aaron's sons handed him the blood, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2966N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2966N\"></sup>threw it against the sides of the altar.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2967O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2967O\"></sup>And they handed the burnt offering to him, piece by piece, and the head, and he burned them on the altar.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2968P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2968P\"></sup>And he washed the entrails and the legs and burned them with the burnt offering on the altar.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2969Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2969Q\"></sup>Then he presented the people's offering and took the goat of the sin offering that was for the people and killed it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2969R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2969R\"></sup>offered it as a sin offering, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2969S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2969S\"></sup>like the first one.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he presented the burnt offering and offered it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2970T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2970T\"></sup>according to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2970U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2970U\"></sup>rule.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he presented the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2971V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2971V\"></sup>grain offering, took a handful of it, and burned it on the altar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2971W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2971W\"></sup>besides the burnt offering of the morning.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then he killed the ox and the ram, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2972X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2972X\"></sup>the sacrifice of peace offerings for the people. And Aaron's sons handed him the blood, and he threw it against the sides of the altar.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But the fat pieces of the ox and of the ram, the fat tail and that which covers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2973Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2973Y\"></sup>the entrails and the kidneys and the long lobe of the liver—",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>they put the fat pieces on the breasts, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2974Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2974Z\"></sup>and he burned the fat pieces on the altar,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>but the breasts and the right thigh Aaron waved <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2975AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2975AA\"></sup>for a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as Moses commanded.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Aaron <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2976AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2976AB\"></sup>lifted up his hands toward the people and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2976AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2976AC\"></sup>blessed them, and he came down from offering the sin offering and the burnt offering and the peace offerings.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Moses and Aaron went into the tent of meeting, and when they came out they blessed the people, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2977AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2977AD\"></sup>the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to all the people.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2978AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2978AE\"></sup>fire came out from before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and consumed the burnt offering and the pieces of fat on the altar, and when all the people saw it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2978AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2978AF\"></sup>they shouted and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2978AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2978AG\"></sup>fell on their faces."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2979A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2979A\"></sup>Nadab and Abihu, the sons of Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2979B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2979B\"></sup>each took his censer and put fire in it and laid incense on it and offered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2979C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2979C\"></sup>unauthorized fire before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which he had not commanded them.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And fire <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2980D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2980D\"></sup>came out from before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and consumed them, and they died before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Moses said to Aaron, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said: ‘Among <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2981E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2981E\"></sup>those who are near me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2981F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2981F\"></sup>I will be sanctified, and before all the people I will be glorified.’” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2981G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2981G\"></sup>And Aaron held his peace.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Moses called Mishael and Elzaphan, the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2982H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2982H\"></sup>Uzziel the uncle of Aaron, and said to them, “Come near; carry your brothers away from the front of the sanctuary and out of the camp.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So they came near and carried them in their coats out of the camp, as Moses had said.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Moses said to Aaron and to Eleazar and Ithamar his sons, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2984I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2984I\"></sup>“Do not let the hair of your heads hang loose, and do not tear your clothes, lest you die, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2984J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2984J\"></sup>wrath come upon all the congregation; but let your brothers, the whole house of Israel, bewail the burning that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has kindled.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2985K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2985K\"></sup>And do not go outside the entrance of the tent of meeting, lest you die, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2985L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2985L\"></sup>for the anointing oil of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is upon you.” And they did according to the word of Moses.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Aaron, saying,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2987M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2987M\"></sup>“Drink no wine or strong drink, you or your sons with you, when you go into the tent of meeting, lest you die. It shall be a statute forever throughout your generations.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You are to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2988N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2988N\"></sup>distinguish between the holy and the common, and between the unclean and the clean,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2989O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2989O\"></sup>you are to teach the people of Israel all the statutes that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken to them by Moses.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Moses spoke to Aaron and to Eleazar and Ithamar, his surviving sons: “Take the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2990P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2990P\"></sup>grain offering that is left of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s food offerings, and eat it unleavened beside the altar, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2990Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2990Q\"></sup>it is most holy.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You shall eat it in a holy place, because it is your due and your sons' due, from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s food offerings, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2991R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2991R\"></sup>so I am commanded.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2992S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2992S\"></sup>breast that is waved and the thigh that is contributed you shall eat in a clean place, you and your sons and your daughters with you, for they are given as your due and your sons' due from the sacrifices of the peace offerings of the people of Israel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2993T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2993T\"></sup>The thigh that is contributed and the breast that is waved they shall bring with the food offerings of the fat pieces to wave for a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and it shall be yours and your sons' with you as a due forever, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now Moses diligently inquired about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2994U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2994U\"></sup>the goat of the sin offering, and behold, it was burned up! And he was angry with Eleazar and Ithamar, the surviving sons of Aaron, saying,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2995V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2995V\"></sup>“Why have you not eaten the sin offering in the place of the sanctuary, since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2995W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2995W\"></sup>it is a thing most holy and has been given to you that you may bear the iniquity of the congregation, to make atonement for them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2996X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2996X\"></sup>its blood was not brought into the inner part of the sanctuary. You certainly ought to have eaten it in the sanctuary, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2996Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2996Y\"></sup>as I commanded.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Aaron said to Moses, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2997Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2997Z\"></sup>today they have offered their sin offering and their burnt offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and yet such things as these have happened to me! If I had eaten the sin offering today, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2997AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2997AA\"></sup>would the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> have approved?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And when Moses heard that, he approved."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying to them,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3000A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3000A\"></sup>These are the living things that you may eat among all the animals that are on the earth.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Whatever parts the hoof and is cloven-footed and chews the cud, among the animals, you may eat.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Nevertheless, among those that chew the cud or part the hoof, you shall not eat these: The camel, because it chews the cud but does not part the hoof, is unclean to you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3003B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3003B\"></sup>rock badger, because it chews the cud but does not part the hoof, is unclean to you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the hare, because it chews the cud but does not part the hoof, is unclean to you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the pig, because it parts the hoof and is cloven-footed but does not chew the cud, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3005C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3005C\"></sup>is unclean to you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You shall not eat any of their flesh, and you shall not touch their carcasses; they are unclean to you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“These you may eat, of all that are in the waters. Everything in the waters that has fins and scales, whether in the seas or in the rivers, you may eat.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But anything in the seas or the rivers that does not have fins and scales, of the swarming creatures in the waters and of the living creatures that are in the waters, is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3008D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3008D\"></sup>detestable to you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You shall regard them as detestable; you shall not eat any of their flesh, and you shall detest their carcasses.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Everything in the waters that does not have fins and scales is detestable to you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“And these you shall detest among the birds; they shall not be eaten; they are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3011E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3011E\"></sup>detestable: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3011F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3011F\"></sup>the eagle, the bearded vulture, the black vulture,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the kite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3012G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3012G\"></sup>the falcon of any kind,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>every raven of any kind,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the ostrich, the nighthawk, the sea gull, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3014H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3014H\"></sup>hawk of any kind,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3015I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3015I\"></sup>little owl, the cormorant, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3015J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3015J\"></sup>short-eared owl,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the barn owl, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3016K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3016K\"></sup>tawny owl, the carrion vulture,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>the stork, the heron of any kind, the hoopoe, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3017L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3017L\"></sup>the bat.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“All winged insects that go on all fours are detestable to you.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Yet among the winged insects that go on all fours you may eat those that have jointed legs above their feet, with which to hop on the ground.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Of them you may eat: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3020M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3020M\"></sup>the locust of any kind, the bald locust of any kind, the cricket of any kind, and the grasshopper of any kind.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But all other winged insects that have four feet are detestable to you.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“And by these you shall become unclean. Whoever touches their carcass shall be unclean until the evening,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and whoever carries any part of their carcass <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3023N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3023N\"></sup>shall wash his clothes and be unclean until the evening.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Every animal that parts the hoof but is not cloven-footed or does not chew the cud is unclean to you. Everyone who touches them shall be unclean.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And all that walk on their paws, among the animals that go on all fours, are unclean to you. Whoever touches their carcass shall be unclean until the evening,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and he who carries their carcass <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3026O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3026O\"></sup>shall wash his clothes and be unclean until the evening; they are unclean to you.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“And these are unclean to you among the swarming things that swarm on the ground: the mole rat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3027P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3027P\"></sup>the mouse, the great lizard of any kind,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>the gecko, the monitor lizard, the lizard, the sand lizard, and the chameleon.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>These are unclean to you among all that swarm. Whoever touches them when they are dead shall be unclean until the evening.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And anything on which any of them falls when they are dead shall be unclean, whether it is an article of wood or a garment or a skin or a sack, any article that is used for any purpose. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3030Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3030Q\"></sup>It must be put into water, and it shall be unclean until the evening; then it shall be clean.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And if any of them falls into any earthenware vessel, all that is in it shall be unclean, and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3031R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3031R\"></sup>shall break it.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Any food in it that could be eaten, on which water comes, shall be unclean. And all drink that could be drunk from every such vessel shall be unclean.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And everything on which any part of their carcass falls shall be unclean. Whether oven or stove, it shall be broken in pieces. They are unclean and shall remain unclean for you.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Nevertheless, a spring or a cistern holding water shall be clean, but whoever touches a carcass in them shall be unclean.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And if any part of their carcass falls upon any seed grain that is to be sown, it is clean,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>but if water is put on the seed and any part of their carcass falls on it, it is unclean to you.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“And if any animal which you may eat dies, whoever touches its carcass shall be unclean until the evening,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3038S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3038S\"></sup>whoever eats of its carcass shall wash his clothes and be unclean until the evening. And whoever carries the carcass shall wash his clothes and be unclean until the evening.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3039T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3039T\"></sup>“Every swarming thing that swarms on the ground is detestable; it shall not be eaten.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Whatever goes on its belly, and whatever goes on all fours, or whatever has many feet, any swarming thing that swarms on the ground, you shall not eat, for they are detestable.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3041U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3041U\"></sup>You shall not make yourselves detestable with any swarming thing that swarms, and you shall not defile yourselves with them, and become unclean through them.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>For I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. Consecrate yourselves therefore, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3042V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3042V\"></sup>be holy, for I am holy. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3042W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3042W\"></sup>You shall not defile yourselves with any swarming thing that crawls on the ground.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3043X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3043X\"></sup>For I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who brought you up out of the land of Egypt to be your God. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3043Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3043Y\"></sup>You shall therefore be holy, for I am holy.”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>This is the law about beast and bird and every living creature that moves through the waters and every creature that swarms on the ground,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3045Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3045Z\"></sup>to make a distinction between the unclean and the clean and between the living creature that may be eaten and the living creature that may not be eaten."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel, saying, If a woman conceives and bears a male child, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3047A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3047A\"></sup>she shall be unclean seven days. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3047B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3047B\"></sup>As at the time of her menstruation, she shall be unclean.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3048C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3048C\"></sup>eighth day the flesh of his foreskin shall be circumcised.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then she shall continue for thirty-three days in the blood of her purifying. She shall not touch anything holy, nor come into the sanctuary, until the days of her purifying are completed.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But if she bears a female child, then she shall be unclean two weeks, as in her menstruation. And she shall continue in the blood of her purifying for sixty-six days.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3051D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3051D\"></sup>“And when the days of her purifying are completed, whether for a son or for a daughter, she shall bring to the priest at the entrance of the tent of meeting a lamb a year old for a burnt offering, and a pigeon or a turtledove for a sin offering,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and he shall offer it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and make atonement for her. Then she shall be clean from the flow of her blood. This is the law for her who bears a child, either male or female.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And if she cannot afford a lamb, then she shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3053E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3053E\"></sup>two turtledoves or two pigeons, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3053F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3053F\"></sup>one for a burnt offering and the other for a sin offering. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3053G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3053G\"></sup>And the priest shall make atonement for her, and she shall be clean.”"
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“When a person has on the skin of his body a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3055A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3055A\"></sup>swelling or an eruption or a spot, and it turns into a case of leprous disease on the skin of his body, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3055B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3055B\"></sup>then he shall be brought to Aaron the priest or to one of his sons the priests,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and the priest shall examine the diseased area on the skin of his body. And if the hair in the diseased area has turned white and the disease appears to be deeper than the skin of his body, it is a case of leprous disease. When the priest has examined him, he shall pronounce him unclean.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But if the spot is white in the skin of his body and appears no deeper than the skin, and the hair in it has not turned white, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3057C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3057C\"></sup>the priest shall shut up the diseased person for seven days.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the priest shall examine him on the seventh day, and if in his eyes the disease is checked and the disease has not spread in the skin, then the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3058D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3058D\"></sup>priest shall shut him up for another seven days.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the priest shall examine him again on the seventh day, and if the diseased area has faded and the disease has not spread in the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him clean; it is only an eruption. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3059E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3059E\"></sup>he shall wash his clothes and be clean.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But if the eruption spreads in the skin, after he has shown himself to the priest for his cleansing, he shall appear again before the priest.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the priest shall look, and if the eruption has spread in the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him unclean; it is a leprous disease.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“When a man is afflicted with a leprous disease, he shall be brought to the priest,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and the priest shall look. And if there is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3063F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3063F\"></sup>white swelling in the skin that has turned the hair white, and there is raw flesh in the swelling,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>it is a chronic leprous disease in the skin of his body, and the priest shall pronounce him unclean. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3064G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3064G\"></sup>He shall not shut him up, for he is unclean.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And if the leprous disease breaks out in the skin, so that the leprous disease covers all the skin of the diseased person from head to foot, so far as the priest can see,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>then the priest shall look, and if the leprous disease has covered all his body, he shall pronounce him clean of the disease; it has all turned white, and he is clean.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But when raw flesh appears on him, he shall be unclean.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the priest shall examine the raw flesh and pronounce him unclean. Raw flesh is unclean, for it is a leprous disease.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But if the raw flesh recovers and turns white again, then he shall come to the priest,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and the priest shall examine him, and if the disease has turned white, then the priest shall pronounce the diseased person clean; he is clean.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“If there is in the skin of one's body a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3071H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3071H\"></sup>boil and it heals,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and in the place of the boil there comes a white swelling or a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3072I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3072I\"></sup>reddish-white spot, then it shall be shown to the priest.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the priest shall look, and if it appears deeper than the skin and its hair has turned white, then the priest shall pronounce him unclean. It is a case of leprous disease that has broken out in the boil.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But if the priest examines it and there is no white hair in it and it is not deeper than the skin, but has faded, then the priest shall shut him up seven days.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And if it spreads in the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him unclean; it is a disease.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3076J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3076J\"></sup>if the spot remains in one place and does not spread, it is the scar of the boil, and the priest shall pronounce him clean.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Or, when the body has a burn on its skin and the raw flesh of the burn becomes a spot, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3077K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3077K\"></sup>reddish-white or white,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>the priest shall examine it, and if the hair in the spot has turned white and it appears deeper than the skin, then it is a leprous disease. It has broken out in the burn, and the priest shall pronounce him unclean; it is a case of leprous disease.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But if the priest examines it and there is no white hair in the spot and it is no deeper than the skin, but has faded, the priest shall shut him up seven days,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and the priest shall examine him the seventh day. If it is spreading in the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him unclean; it is a case of leprous disease.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But if the spot remains <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3081L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3081L\"></sup>in one place and does not spread in the skin, but has faded, it is a swelling from the burn, and the priest shall pronounce him clean, for it is the scar of the burn.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“When a man or woman has a disease on the head or the beard,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>the priest shall examine the disease. And if it appears deeper than the skin, and the hair in it is yellow and thin, then the priest shall pronounce him unclean. It is an itch, a leprous disease of the head or the beard.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And if the priest examines the itching disease and it appears no deeper than the skin and there is no black hair in it, then the priest shall shut up the person with the itching disease for seven days,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and on the seventh day the priest shall examine the disease. If the itch has not spread, and there is in it no yellow hair, and the itch appears to be no deeper than the skin,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>then he shall shave himself, but the itch he shall not shave; and the priest shall shut up the person with the itching disease for another seven days.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And on the seventh day the priest shall examine the itch, and if the itch has not spread in the skin and it appears to be no deeper than the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him clean. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3087M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3087M\"></sup>he shall wash his clothes and be clean.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But if the itch spreads in the skin after his cleansing,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>then the priest shall examine him, and if the itch has spread in the skin, the priest need not seek for the yellow hair; he is unclean.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>But if in his eyes the itch is unchanged and black hair has grown in it, the itch is healed and he is clean, and the priest shall pronounce him clean.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“When a man or a woman has spots on the skin of the body, white spots,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>the priest shall look, and if the spots on the skin of the body are of a dull white, it is leukoderma that has broken out in the skin; he is clean.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“If a man's hair falls out from his head, he is bald; he is clean.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And if a man's hair falls out from his forehead, he has baldness of the forehead; he is clean.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>But if there is on the bald head or the bald forehead a reddish-white diseased area, it is a leprous disease breaking out on his bald head or his bald forehead.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Then the priest shall examine him, and if the diseased swelling is reddish-white on his bald head or on his bald forehead, like the appearance of leprous disease in the skin of the body,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>he is a leprous man, he is unclean. The priest must pronounce him unclean; his disease is on his head.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>“The leprous person who has the disease shall wear torn clothes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3098N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3098N\"></sup>let the hair of his head hang loose, and he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3098O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3098O\"></sup>cover his upper lip and cry out, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3098P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3098P\"></sup>‘Unclean, unclean.’",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>He shall remain unclean as long as he has the disease. He is unclean. He shall live alone. His dwelling shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3099Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3099Q\"></sup>outside the camp.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“When there is a case of leprous disease in a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3100R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3100R\"></sup>garment, whether a woolen or a linen garment,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>in warp or woof of linen or wool, or in a skin or in anything made of skin,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>if the disease is greenish or reddish in the garment, or in the skin or in the warp or the woof or in any article made of skin, it is a case of leprous disease, and it shall be shown to the priest.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>And the priest shall examine the disease and shut up that which has the disease for seven days.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Then he shall examine the disease on the seventh day. If the disease has spread in the garment, in the warp or the woof, or in the skin, whatever be the use of the skin, the disease is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3104S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3104S\"></sup>persistent leprous disease; it is unclean.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>And he shall burn the garment, or the warp or the woof, the wool or the linen, or any article made of skin that is diseased, for it is a persistent leprous disease. It shall be burned in the fire.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>“And if the priest examines, and if the disease has not spread in the garment, in the warp or the woof or in any article made of skin,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>then the priest shall command that they wash the thing in which is the disease, and he shall shut it up for another seven days.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>And the priest shall examine the diseased thing after it has been washed. And if the appearance of the diseased area has not changed, though the disease has not spread, it is unclean. You shall burn it in the fire, whether the rot is on the back or on the front.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>“But if the priest examines, and if the diseased area has faded after it has been washed, he shall tear it out of the garment or the skin or the warp or the woof.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>Then if it appears again in the garment, in the warp or the woof, or in any article made of skin, it is spreading. You shall burn with fire whatever has the disease.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>But the garment, or the warp or the woof, or any article made of skin from which the disease departs when you have washed it, shall then be washed a second time, and be clean.”",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>This is the law for a case of leprous disease in a garment of wool or linen, either in the warp or the woof, or in any article made of skin, to determine whether it is clean or unclean."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“This shall be the law of the leprous person for the day of his cleansing. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3114A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3114A\"></sup>He shall be brought to the priest,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and the priest shall go <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3115B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3115B\"></sup>out of the camp, and the priest shall look. Then, if the case of leprous disease is healed in the leprous person,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>the priest shall command them to take for him who is to be cleansed two live clean birds and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3116C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3116C\"></sup>cedarwood and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3116D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3116D\"></sup>scarlet yarn and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3116E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3116E\"></sup>hyssop.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the priest shall command them to kill one of the birds in an earthenware vessel over fresh water.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He shall take the live bird with the cedarwood and the scarlet yarn and the hyssop, and dip them and the live bird in the blood of the bird that was killed over the fresh water.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3119F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3119F\"></sup>sprinkle it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3119G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3119G\"></sup>seven times on him who is to be cleansed of the leprous disease. Then he shall pronounce him clean and shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3119H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3119H\"></sup>let the living bird go <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3119I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3119I\"></sup>into the open field.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he who is to be cleansed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3120J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3120J\"></sup>shall wash his clothes and shave off all his hair and bathe himself in water, and he shall be clean. And after that he may come into the camp, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3120K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3120K\"></sup>live outside his tent seven days.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3121L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3121L\"></sup>on the seventh day he shall shave off all his hair from his head, his beard, and his eyebrows. He shall shave off all his hair, and then he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3121M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3121M\"></sup>shall wash his clothes and bathe his body in water, and he shall be clean.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“And on the eighth day he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3122N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3122N\"></sup>shall take two male lambs without blemish, and one ewe lamb a year old without blemish, and a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3122O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3122O\"></sup>grain offering of three tenths of an ephah of fine flour mixed with oil, and one log of oil.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the priest who cleanses him shall set the man who is to be cleansed and these things before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, at the entrance of the tent of meeting.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the priest shall take one of the male lambs and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3124P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3124P\"></sup>offer it for a guilt offering, along with the log of oil, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3124Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3124Q\"></sup>wave them for a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And he shall kill the lamb <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3125R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3125R\"></sup>in the place where they kill the sin offering and the burnt offering, in the place of the sanctuary. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3125S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3125S\"></sup>the guilt offering, like the sin offering, belongs to the priest; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3125T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3125T\"></sup>it is most holy.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The priest shall take some of the blood of the guilt offering, and the priest shall put it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3126U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3126U\"></sup>on the lobe of the right ear of him who is to be cleansed and on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the priest shall take some of the log of oil and pour it into the palm of his own left hand",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and dip his right finger in the oil that is in his left hand and sprinkle some oil with his finger seven times before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And some of the oil that remains in his hand the priest shall put on the lobe of the right ear of him who is to be cleansed and on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot, on top of the blood of the guilt offering.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the rest of the oil that is in the priest's hand he shall put on the head of him who is to be cleansed. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3130V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3130V\"></sup>Then the priest shall make atonement for him before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The priest shall offer the sin offering, to make atonement for him who is to be cleansed from his uncleanness. And afterward he shall kill the burnt offering.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the priest shall offer the burnt offering and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3132W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3132W\"></sup>grain offering on the altar. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3132X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3132X\"></sup>Thus the priest shall make atonement for him, and he shall be clean.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3133Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3133Y\"></sup>if he is poor and cannot afford so much, then he shall take one male lamb for a guilt offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3133Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3133Z\"></sup>to be waved, to make atonement for him, and a tenth of an ephah of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering, and a log of oil;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3134AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3134AA\"></sup>also two turtledoves or two pigeons, whichever he can afford. The one shall be a sin offering and the other a burnt offering.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3135AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3135AB\"></sup>And on the eighth day he shall bring them for his cleansing to the priest, to the entrance of the tent of meeting, before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3136AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3136AC\"></sup>And the priest shall take the lamb of the guilt offering and the log of oil, and the priest shall wave them for a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And he shall kill the lamb of the guilt offering. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3137AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3137AD\"></sup>And the priest shall take some of the blood of the guilt offering and put it on the lobe of the right ear of him who is to be cleansed, and on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And the priest shall pour some of the oil into the palm of his own left hand,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and shall sprinkle with his right finger some of the oil that is in his left hand seven times before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And the priest shall put some of the oil that is in his hand on the lobe of the right ear of him who is to be cleansed and on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot, in the place where the blood of the guilt offering was put.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And the rest of the oil that is in the priest's hand he shall put on the head of him who is to be cleansed, to make atonement for him before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And he shall offer, of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3142AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3142AE\"></sup>turtledoves or pigeons, whichever he can afford,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering, along with a grain offering. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3143AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3143AF\"></sup>And the priest shall make atonement before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for him who is being cleansed.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>This is the law for him in whom is a case of leprous disease, who cannot afford <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3144AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3144AG\"></sup>the offerings for his cleansing.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“When you come into the land of Canaan, which I give you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3146AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3146AH\"></sup>for a possession, and I put a case of leprous disease in a house in the land of your possession,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>then he who owns the house shall come and tell the priest, ‘There seems to me to be some case of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3147AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3147AI\"></sup>disease in my house.’",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then the priest shall command that they empty the house before the priest goes to examine the disease, lest all that is in the house be declared unclean. And afterward the priest shall go in to see the house.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And he shall examine the disease. And if the disease is in the walls of the house with greenish or reddish spots, and if it appears to be deeper than the surface,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>then the priest shall go out of the house to the door of the house and shut up the house seven days.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And the priest shall come again on the seventh day, and look. If the disease has spread in the walls of the house,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>then the priest shall command that they take out the stones in which is the disease and throw them into an unclean place outside the city.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And he shall have the inside of the house scraped all around, and the plaster that they scrape off they shall pour out in an unclean place outside the city.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Then they shall take other stones and put them in the place of those stones, and he shall take other plaster and plaster the house.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>“If the disease breaks out again in the house, after he has taken out the stones and scraped the house and plastered it,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>then the priest shall go and look. And if the disease has spread in the house, it is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3156AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3156AJ\"></sup>persistent leprous disease in the house; it is unclean.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>And he shall break down the house, its stones and timber and all the plaster of the house, and he shall carry them out of the city to an unclean place.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Moreover, whoever enters the house while it is shut up shall be unclean until the evening,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>and whoever sleeps in the house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3159AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3159AK\"></sup>shall wash his clothes, and whoever eats in the house shall wash his clothes.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>“But if the priest comes and looks, and if the disease has not spread in the house after the house was plastered, then the priest shall pronounce the house clean, for the disease is healed.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>And for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3161AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3161AL\"></sup>cleansing of the house he shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3161AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3161AM\"></sup>two small birds, with cedarwood and scarlet yarn and hyssop,",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>and shall kill one of the birds in an earthenware vessel over fresh water",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>and shall take the cedarwood and the hyssop and the scarlet yarn, along with the live bird, and dip them in the blood of the bird that was killed and in the fresh water and sprinkle the house seven times.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Thus he shall cleanse the house with the blood of the bird and with the fresh water and with the live bird and with the cedarwood and hyssop and scarlet yarn.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>And he shall let the live bird go out of the city <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3165AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3165AN\"></sup>into the open country. So he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3165AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3165AO\"></sup>make atonement for the house, and it shall be clean.”",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>This is the law for any case of leprous disease: for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3166AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3166AP\"></sup>an itch,",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3167AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3167AQ\"></sup>leprous disease in a garment or in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3167AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3167AR\"></sup>a house,",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3168AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3168AS\"></sup>for a swelling or an eruption or a spot,",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3169AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3169AT\"></sup>show when it is unclean and when it is clean. This is the law for leprous disease."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel and say to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3171A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3171A\"></sup>When any man has a discharge from his body, his discharge is unclean.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And this is the law of his uncleanness for a discharge: whether his body runs with his discharge, or his body is blocked up by his discharge, it is his uncleanness.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Every bed on which the one with the discharge lies shall be unclean, and everything on which he sits shall be unclean.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And anyone who touches his bed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3174B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3174B\"></sup>shall wash his clothes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3174C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3174C\"></sup>bathe himself in water and be unclean until the evening.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And whoever sits on anything on which the one with the discharge has sat shall wash his clothes and bathe himself in water and be unclean until the evening.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And whoever touches the body of the one with the discharge shall wash his clothes and bathe himself in water and be unclean until the evening.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And if the one with the discharge spits on someone who is clean, then he shall wash his clothes and bathe himself in water and be unclean until the evening.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And any saddle on which the one with the discharge rides shall be unclean.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And whoever touches anything that was under him shall be unclean until the evening. And whoever carries such things shall wash his clothes and bathe himself in water and be unclean until the evening.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Anyone whom the one with the discharge touches without having rinsed his hands in water shall wash his clothes and bathe himself in water and be unclean until the evening.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3181D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3181D\"></sup>earthenware vessel that the one with the discharge touches shall be broken, and every vessel of wood shall be rinsed in water.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“And when the one with a discharge is cleansed of his discharge, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3182E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3182E\"></sup>he shall count for himself seven days for his cleansing, and wash his clothes. And he shall bathe his body in fresh water and shall be clean.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And on the eighth day he shall take two <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3183F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3183F\"></sup>turtledoves or two pigeons and come before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to the entrance of the tent of meeting and give them to the priest.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the priest shall use them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3184G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3184G\"></sup>one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3184H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3184H\"></sup>And the priest shall make atonement for him before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for his discharge.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3185I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3185I\"></sup>“If a man has an emission of semen, he shall bathe his whole body in water and be unclean until the evening.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And every garment and every skin on which the semen comes shall be washed with water and be unclean until the evening.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>If a man lies with a woman and has an emission of semen, both of them shall bathe themselves in water and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3187J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3187J\"></sup>be unclean until the evening.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“When a woman has a discharge, and the discharge in her body is blood, she shall be in her menstrual impurity for seven days, and whoever touches her shall be unclean until the evening.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3189K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3189K\"></sup>And everything on which she lies during her menstrual impurity shall be unclean. Everything also on which she sits shall be unclean.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And whoever touches her bed shall wash his clothes and bathe himself in water and be unclean until the evening.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And whoever touches anything on which she sits shall wash his clothes and bathe himself in water and be unclean until the evening.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Whether it is the bed or anything on which she sits, when he touches it he shall be unclean until the evening.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3193L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3193L\"></sup>if any man lies with her and her menstrual impurity comes upon him, he shall be unclean seven days, and every bed on which he lies shall be unclean.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“If <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3194M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3194M\"></sup>a woman has a discharge of blood for many days, not at the time of her menstrual impurity, or if she has a discharge beyond the time of her impurity, all the days of the discharge she shall continue in uncleanness. As in the days of her impurity, she shall be unclean.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Every bed on which she lies, all the days of her discharge, shall be to her as the bed of her impurity. And everything on which she sits shall be unclean, as in the uncleanness of her menstrual impurity.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And whoever touches these things shall be unclean, and shall wash his clothes and bathe himself in water and be unclean until the evening.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3197N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3197N\"></sup>if she is cleansed of her discharge, she shall count for herself seven days, and after that she shall be clean.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And on the eighth day she shall take two <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3198O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3198O\"></sup>turtledoves or two pigeons and bring them to the priest, to the entrance of the tent of meeting.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the priest shall use one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering. And the priest shall make atonement for her before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for her unclean discharge.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“Thus you shall keep the people of Israel separate from their uncleanness, lest they die in their uncleanness by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3200P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3200P\"></sup>defiling my tabernacle that is in their midst.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>This is the law <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3201Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3201Q\"></sup>for him who has a discharge and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3201R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3201R\"></sup>for him who has an emission of semen, becoming unclean thereby;",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3202S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3202S\"></sup>also for her who is unwell with her menstrual impurity, that is, for anyone, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3202T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3202T\"></sup>male or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3202U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3202U\"></sup>female, who has a discharge, and for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3202V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3202V\"></sup>man who lies with a woman who is unclean."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3203A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3203A\"></sup>the death of the two sons of Aaron, when they drew near before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and died,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Tell Aaron your brother not to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3204B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3204B\"></sup>come at any time into the Holy Place inside the veil, before the mercy seat that is on the ark, so that he may not die. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3204C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3204C\"></sup>I will appear in the cloud over the mercy seat.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But in this way Aaron shall come into the Holy Place: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3205D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3205D\"></sup>with a bull from the herd for a sin offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3205E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3205E\"></sup>a ram for a burnt offering.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He shall put on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3206F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3206F\"></sup>the holy linen coat and shall have the linen undergarment on his body, and he shall tie the linen sash around his waist, and wear the linen turban; these are the holy garments. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3206G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3206G\"></sup>He shall bathe his body in water and then put them on.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he shall take from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3207H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3207H\"></sup>the congregation of the people of Israel two male goats for a sin offering, and one ram for a burnt offering.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Aaron shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3208I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3208I\"></sup>offer the bull as a sin offering for himself and shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3208J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3208J\"></sup>make atonement for himself and for his house.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then he shall take the two goats and set them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at the entrance of the tent of meeting.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Aaron shall cast lots over the two goats, one lot for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the other lot for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3210K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3210K\"></sup>Azazel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Aaron shall present the goat on which the lot fell for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and use it as a sin offering,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>but the goat on which the lot fell for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3212L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3212L\"></sup>Azazel shall be presented alive before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to make atonement over it, that it may be sent away into the wilderness to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3212M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3212M\"></sup>Azazel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Aaron shall present <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3213N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3213N\"></sup>the bull as a sin offering for himself, and shall make atonement for himself and for his house. He shall kill the bull as a sin offering for himself.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3214O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3214O\"></sup>a censer full of coals of fire from the altar before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and two handfuls of sweet incense beaten small, and he shall bring it inside the veil",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3215P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3215P\"></sup>and put the incense on the fire before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that the cloud of the incense may cover <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3215Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3215Q\"></sup>the mercy seat that is over the testimony, so that he does not die.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3216R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3216R\"></sup>he shall take some of the blood of the bull and sprinkle it with his finger on the front of the mercy seat on the east side, and in front of the mercy seat he shall sprinkle some of the blood with his finger seven times.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3217S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3217S\"></sup>“Then he shall kill the goat of the sin offering that is for the people and bring its blood <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3217T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3217T\"></sup>inside the veil and do with its blood as he did with the blood of the bull, sprinkling it over the mercy seat and in front of the mercy seat.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Thus he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3218U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3218U\"></sup>make atonement for the Holy Place, because of the uncleannesses of the people of Israel and because of their transgressions, all their sins. And so he shall do for the tent of meeting, which dwells with them in the midst of their uncleannesses.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3219V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3219V\"></sup>No one may be in the tent of meeting from the time he enters to make atonement in the Holy Place until he comes out and has made atonement for himself and for his house and for all the assembly of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then he shall go out to the altar that is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3220W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3220W\"></sup>before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3220X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3220X\"></sup>make atonement for it, and shall take some of the blood of the bull and some of the blood of the goat, and put it on the horns of the altar all around.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he shall sprinkle some of the blood on it with his finger seven times, and cleanse it and consecrate it from the uncleannesses of the people of Israel.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“And when he has made an end of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3222Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3222Y\"></sup>atoning for the Holy Place and the tent of meeting and the altar, he shall present the live goat.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Aaron shall lay both his hands on the head of the live goat, and confess over it all the iniquities of the people of Israel, and all their transgressions, all their sins. And he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3223Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3223Z\"></sup>put them on the head of the goat and send it away into the wilderness by the hand of a man who is in readiness.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The goat shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3224AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3224AA\"></sup>bear all their iniquities on itself to a remote area, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3224AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3224AB\"></sup>he shall let the goat go free in the wilderness.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Then Aaron shall come into the tent of meeting and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3225AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3225AC\"></sup>shall take off the linen garments that he put on when he went into the Holy Place and shall leave them there.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And he shall bathe his body in water in a holy place and put on his garments and come out and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3226AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3226AD\"></sup>offer his burnt offering and the burnt offering of the people and make atonement for himself and for the people.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3227AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3227AE\"></sup>the fat of the sin offering he shall burn on the altar.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And he who lets the goat go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3228AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3228AF\"></sup>Azazel shall wash his clothes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3228AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3228AG\"></sup>bathe his body in water, and afterward he may come into the camp.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3229AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3229AH\"></sup>And the bull for the sin offering and the goat for the sin offering, whose blood was brought in to make atonement in the Holy Place, shall be carried outside the camp. Their skin and their flesh and their dung shall be burned up with fire.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And he who burns them shall wash his clothes and bathe his body in water, and afterward he may come into the camp.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“And it shall be a statute to you forever that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3231AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3231AI\"></sup>in the seventh month, on the tenth day of the month, you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3231AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3231AJ\"></sup>afflict yourselves and shall do no work, either <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3231AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3231AK\"></sup>the native or the stranger who sojourns among you.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For on this day shall atonement be made for you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3232AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3232AL\"></sup>to cleanse you. You shall be clean before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from all your sins.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3233AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3233AM\"></sup>It is a Sabbath of solemn rest to you, and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3233AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3233AN\"></sup>afflict yourselves; it is a statute forever.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3234AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3234AO\"></sup>And the priest who is anointed and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3234AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3234AP\"></sup>consecrated as priest in his father's place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3234AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3234AQ\"></sup>shall make atonement, wearing the holy linen garments.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He shall make atonement for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3235AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3235AR\"></sup>the holy sanctuary, and he shall make atonement for the tent of meeting and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3235AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3235AS\"></sup>the altar, and he shall make atonement for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3235AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3235AT\"></sup>the priests and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3235AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3235AU\"></sup>all the people of the assembly.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And this shall be a statute forever for you, that atonement may be made for the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3236AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3236AV\"></sup>once in the year because of all their sins.” And Aaron did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to Aaron and his sons and to all the people of Israel and say to them, This is the thing that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>If any one of the house of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3239A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3239A\"></sup>kills an ox or a lamb or a goat in the camp, or kills it outside the camp,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3240B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3240B\"></sup>does not bring it to the entrance of the tent of meeting to offer it as a gift to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in front of the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, bloodguilt shall be imputed to that man. He has shed blood, and that man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3240C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3240C\"></sup>shall be cut off from among his people.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>This is to the end that the people of Israel may bring their sacrifices that they sacrifice <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3241D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3241D\"></sup>in the open field, that they may bring them to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to the priest at the entrance of the tent of meeting, and sacrifice them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3241E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3241E\"></sup>as sacrifices of peace offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the priest shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3242F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3242F\"></sup>throw the blood on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at the entrance of the tent of meeting and burn the fat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3242G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3242G\"></sup>for a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So they shall no more sacrifice their sacrifices to goat demons, after whom they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3243H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3243H\"></sup>whore. This shall be a statute forever for them throughout their generations.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“And you shall say to them, Any one of the house of Israel, or of the strangers who sojourn among them, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3244I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3244I\"></sup>offers a burnt offering or sacrifice",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3245J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3245J\"></sup>does not bring it to the entrance of the tent of meeting to offer it to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3245K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3245K\"></sup>that man shall be cut off from his people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“If any one of the house of Israel or of the strangers who sojourn among them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3246L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3246L\"></sup>eats any blood, I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3246M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3246M\"></sup>set my face against that person who eats blood and will cut him off from among his people.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3247N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3247N\"></sup>For the life of the flesh is in the blood, and I have given it for you on the altar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3247O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3247O\"></sup>to make atonement for your souls, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3247P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3247P\"></sup>for it is the blood that makes atonement by the life.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Therefore I have said to the people of Israel, No person among you shall eat blood, neither shall any stranger who sojourns among you eat blood.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Any one also of the people of Israel, or of the strangers who sojourn among them, who takes in hunting any beast or bird that may be eaten shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3249Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3249Q\"></sup>pour out its blood and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3249R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3249R\"></sup>cover it with earth.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For the life of every creature is its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3250S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3250S\"></sup>blood: its blood is its life. Therefore I have said to the people of Israel, You shall not eat the blood of any creature, for the life of every creature is its blood. Whoever eats it shall be cut off.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3251T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3251T\"></sup>And every person who eats what dies of itself or what is torn by beasts, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3251U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3251U\"></sup>whether he is a native or a sojourner, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3251V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3251V\"></sup>shall wash his clothes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3251W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3251W\"></sup>bathe himself in water and be unclean until the evening; then he shall be clean.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But if he does not wash them or bathe his flesh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3252X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3252X\"></sup>he shall bear his iniquity.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel and say to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3254A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3254A\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3255B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3255B\"></sup>You shall not do as they do in the land of Egypt, where you lived, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3255C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3255C\"></sup>you shall not do as they do in the land of Canaan, to which I am bringing you. You shall not walk in their statutes.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3256D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3256D\"></sup>You shall follow my rules and keep my statutes and walk in them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3256E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3256E\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3257F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3257F\"></sup>You shall therefore keep my statutes and my rules; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3257G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3257G\"></sup>if a person does them, he shall live by them: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“None of you shall approach any one of his close relatives to uncover nakedness. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3259H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3259H\"></sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your father, which is the nakedness of your mother; she is your mother, you shall not uncover her nakedness.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3260I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3260I\"></sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your father's wife; it is your father's nakedness.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3261J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3261J\"></sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your sister, your father's daughter or your mother's daughter, whether brought up in the family or in another home.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your son's daughter or of your daughter's daughter, for their nakedness is your own nakedness.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your father's wife's daughter, brought up in your father's family, since she is your sister.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your father's sister; she is your father's relative.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your mother's sister, for she is your mother's relative.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your father's brother, that is, you shall not approach his wife; she is your aunt.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3267K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3267K\"></sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your daughter-in-law; she is your son's wife, you shall not uncover her nakedness.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3268L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3268L\"></sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your brother's wife; it is your brother's nakedness.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of a woman and of her daughter, and you shall not take her son's daughter or her daughter's daughter to uncover her nakedness; they are relatives; it is depravity.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And you shall not take a woman as a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3270M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3270M\"></sup>rival wife to her sister, uncovering her nakedness <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3270N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3270N\"></sup>while her sister is still alive.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3271O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3271O\"></sup>“You shall not approach a woman to uncover her nakedness while she is in her menstrual uncleanness.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3272P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3272P\"></sup>And you shall not lie sexually with your neighbor's wife and so make yourself unclean with her.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>You shall not give any of your children to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3273Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3273Q\"></sup>offer them to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3273R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3273R\"></sup>Molech, and so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3273S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3273S\"></sup>profane the name of your God: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3274T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3274T\"></sup>You shall not lie with a male as with a woman; it is an abomination.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3275U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3275U\"></sup>And you shall not lie with any animal and so make yourself unclean with it, neither shall any woman give herself to an animal to lie with it: it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3275V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3275V\"></sup>perversion.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3276W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3276W\"></sup>“Do not make yourselves unclean by any of these things, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3276X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3276X\"></sup>for by all these the nations I am driving out before you have become unclean,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3277Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3277Y\"></sup>land became unclean, so that I punished its iniquity, and the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3277Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3277Z\"></sup>vomited out its inhabitants.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3278AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3278AA\"></sup>you shall keep my statutes and my rules and do none of these abominations, either the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3278AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3278AB\"></sup>native or the stranger who sojourns among you",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>(for the people of the land, who were before you, did all of these abominations, so that the land became unclean),",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>lest the land vomit you out when you make it unclean, as it vomited out the nation that was before you.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>For everyone who does any of these abominations, the persons who do them shall be cut off from among their people.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3282AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3282AC\"></sup>So keep my charge never to practice <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3282AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3282AD\"></sup>any of these abominable customs that were practiced before you, and never to make yourselves unclean by them: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3282AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3282AE\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.”"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to all the congregation of the people of Israel and say to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3284A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3284A\"></sup>You shall be holy, for I the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God am holy.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3285B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3285B\"></sup>Every one of you shall revere his mother and his father, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3285C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3285C\"></sup>you shall keep my Sabbaths: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3286D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3286D\"></sup>Do not turn to idols <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3286E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3286E\"></sup>or make for yourselves any gods of cast metal: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3287F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3287F\"></sup>“When you offer a sacrifice of peace offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you shall offer it so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3287G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3287G\"></sup>that you may be accepted.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>It shall be eaten the same day you offer it or on the day after, and anything left over until the third day shall be burned up with fire.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If it is eaten at all on the third day, it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3289H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3289H\"></sup>tainted; it will not be accepted,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and everyone who eats it shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3290I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3290I\"></sup>bear his iniquity, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3290J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3290J\"></sup>he has profaned what is holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and that person shall be cut off from his people.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3291K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3291K\"></sup>“When you reap the harvest of your land, you shall not reap your field right up to its edge, neither shall you gather the gleanings after your harvest.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And you shall not strip your vineyard bare, neither shall you gather the fallen grapes of your vineyard. You shall leave them for the poor and for the sojourner: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3293L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3293L\"></sup>“You shall not steal; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3293M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3293M\"></sup>you shall not deal falsely; you shall not lie to one another.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3294N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3294N\"></sup>You shall not swear by my name falsely, and so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3294O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3294O\"></sup>profane the name of your God: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3295P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3295P\"></sup>“You shall not oppress your neighbor or rob him. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3295Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3295Q\"></sup>The wages of a hired worker shall not remain with you all night until the morning.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3296R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3296R\"></sup>You shall not curse the deaf or put a stumbling block before the blind, but you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3296S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3296S\"></sup>fear your God: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3297T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3297T\"></sup>“You shall do no injustice in court. You shall not be partial to the poor or defer to the great, but in righteousness shall you judge your neighbor.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3298U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3298U\"></sup>You shall not go around as a slanderer among your people, and you shall not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3298V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3298V\"></sup>stand up against the life of your neighbor: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3299W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3299W\"></sup>“You shall not hate your brother in your heart, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3299X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3299X\"></sup>you shall reason frankly with your neighbor, lest you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3299Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3299Y\"></sup>incur sin because of him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3300Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3300Z\"></sup>You shall not take vengeance or bear a grudge against the sons of your own people, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3300AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3300AA\"></sup>you shall love your neighbor as yourself: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3301AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3301AB\"></sup>“You shall keep my statutes. You shall not let your cattle breed with a different kind. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3301AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3301AC\"></sup>You shall not sow your field with two kinds of seed, nor shall you wear a garment of cloth made of two kinds of material.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“If a man lies sexually with a woman who is a slave, assigned to another man and not yet ransomed or given her freedom, a distinction shall be made. They shall not be put to death, because she was not free;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3303AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3303AD\"></sup>he shall bring his compensation to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to the entrance of the tent of meeting, a ram for a guilt offering.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And the priest shall make atonement for him with the ram of the guilt offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for his sin that he has committed, and he shall be forgiven for the sin that he has committed.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“When you come into the land and plant any kind of tree for food, then you shall regard its fruit as forbidden. Three years it shall be forbidden to you; it must not be eaten.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And in the fourth year all its fruit shall be holy, an offering of praise to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But in the fifth year you may eat of its fruit, to increase its yield for you: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3308AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3308AE\"></sup>“You shall not eat any flesh with the blood in it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3308AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3308AF\"></sup>You shall not interpret omens or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3308AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3308AG\"></sup>tell fortunes.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3309AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3309AH\"></sup>You shall not round off the hair on your temples or mar the edges of your beard.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>You shall not make any <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3310AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3310AI\"></sup>cuts on your body for the dead or tattoo yourselves: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3311AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3311AJ\"></sup>“Do not profane your daughter by making her a prostitute, lest the land fall into prostitution and the land become full of depravity.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3312AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3312AK\"></sup>You shall keep my Sabbaths and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3312AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3312AL\"></sup>reverence my sanctuary: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3313AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3313AM\"></sup>“Do not turn to mediums or necromancers; do not seek them out, and so make yourselves unclean by them: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3314AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3314AN\"></sup>“You shall stand up before the gray head and honor the face of an old man, and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3314AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3314AO\"></sup>fear your God: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3315AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3315AP\"></sup>“When a stranger sojourns with you in your land, you shall not do him wrong.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3316AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3316AQ\"></sup>You shall treat the stranger who sojourns with you as the native among you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3316AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3316AR\"></sup>you shall love him as yourself, for you were strangers in the land of Egypt: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3317AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3317AS\"></sup>“You shall do no wrong in judgment, in measures of length or weight or quantity.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3318AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3318AT\"></sup>You shall have just balances, just weights, a just ephah, and a just hin: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3319AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3319AU\"></sup>you shall observe all my statutes and all my rules, and do them: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”"
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Say to the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3321A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3321A\"></sup>Any one of the people of Israel or of the strangers who sojourn in Israel who gives any of his children to Molech shall surely be put to death. The people of the land shall stone him with stones.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3322B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3322B\"></sup>I myself will set my face against that man and will cut him off from among his people, because he has given one of his children to Molech, to make my sanctuary <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3322C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3322C\"></sup>unclean and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3322D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3322D\"></sup>to profane my holy name.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And if the people of the land do at all close their eyes to that man when he gives one of his children to Molech, and do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3323E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3323E\"></sup>put him to death,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>then I will set my face against that man and against his clan and will cut them off from among their people, him and all who follow him in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3324F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3324F\"></sup>whoring after Molech.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“If <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3325G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3325G\"></sup>a person turns to mediums and necromancers, whoring after them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3325H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3325H\"></sup>I will set my face against that person and will cut him off from among his people.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3326I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3326I\"></sup>Consecrate yourselves, therefore, and be holy, for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3327J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3327J\"></sup>Keep my statutes and do them; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3327K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3327K\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who sanctifies you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3328L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3328L\"></sup>anyone who curses his father or his mother shall surely be put to death; he has cursed his father or his mother; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3328M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3328M\"></sup>his blood is upon him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“If a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3329N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3329N\"></sup>man commits adultery with the wife of his neighbor, both the adulterer and the adulteress shall surely be put to death.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3330O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3330O\"></sup>If a man lies with his father's wife, he has uncovered his father's nakedness; both of them shall surely be put to death; their blood is upon them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3331P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3331P\"></sup>If a man lies with his daughter-in-law, both of them shall surely be put to death; they have committed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3331Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3331Q\"></sup>perversion; their blood is upon them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3332R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3332R\"></sup>If a man lies with a male as with a woman, both of them have committed an abomination; they shall surely be put to death; their blood is upon them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3333S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3333S\"></sup>If a man takes a woman and her mother also, it is depravity; he and they shall be burned with fire, that there may be no depravity among you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3334T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3334T\"></sup>If a man lies with an animal, he shall surely be put to death, and you shall kill the animal.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3335U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3335U\"></sup>If a woman approaches any animal and lies with it, you shall kill the woman and the animal; they shall surely be put to death; their blood is upon them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3336V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3336V\"></sup>“If a man takes his sister, a daughter of his father or a daughter of his mother, and sees her nakedness, and she sees his nakedness, it is a disgrace, and they shall be cut off in the sight of the children of their people. He has uncovered his sister's nakedness, and he shall bear his iniquity.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3337W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3337W\"></sup>If a man lies with a woman during her menstrual period and uncovers her nakedness, he has made naked her fountain, and she has uncovered the fountain of her blood. Both of them shall be cut off from among their people.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3338X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3338X\"></sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your mother's sister or of your father's sister, for that is to make naked <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3338Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3338Y\"></sup>one's relative; they shall bear their iniquity.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3339Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3339Z\"></sup>If a man lies with his uncle's wife, he has uncovered his uncle's nakedness; they shall bear their sin; they shall die childless.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3340AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3340AA\"></sup>If a man takes his brother's wife, it is impurity. He has uncovered his brother's nakedness; they shall be childless.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3341AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3341AB\"></sup>“You shall therefore keep all my statutes and all my rules and do them, that the land where I am bringing you to live may not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3341AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3341AC\"></sup>vomit you out.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3342AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3342AD\"></sup>And you shall not walk in the customs of the nation that I am driving out before you, for they did all these things, and therefore I detested them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3343AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3343AE\"></sup>I have said to you, ‘You shall inherit their land, and I will give it to you to possess, a land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3343AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3343AF\"></sup>flowing with milk and honey.’ I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3343AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3343AG\"></sup>who has separated you from the peoples.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3344AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3344AH\"></sup>You shall therefore separate the clean beast from the unclean, and the unclean bird from the clean. You shall not make yourselves detestable by beast or by bird or by anything with which the ground crawls, which I have set apart for you to hold unclean.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3345AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3345AI\"></sup>You shall be holy to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3345AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3345AJ\"></sup>for I the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> am holy and have separated you from the peoples, that you should be mine.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3346AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3346AK\"></sup>“A man or a woman who is a medium or a necromancer shall surely be put to death. They shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3346AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3346AL\"></sup>stoned with stones; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3346AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3346AM\"></sup>their blood shall be upon them.”"
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Speak to the priests, the sons of Aaron, and say to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3347A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3347A\"></sup>No one shall make himself unclean for the dead among his people,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>except for his closest relatives, his mother, his father, his son, his daughter, his brother,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>or his virgin sister (who is near to him because she has had no husband; for her he may make himself unclean).",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He shall not make himself unclean as a husband among his people and so profane himself.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3351B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3351B\"></sup>They shall not make bald patches on their heads, nor shave off the edges of their beards, nor make any cuts on their body.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They shall be holy to their God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3352C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3352C\"></sup>not profane the name of their God. For they offer the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s food offerings, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3352D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3352D\"></sup>the bread of their God; therefore they shall be holy.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3353E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3353E\"></sup>They shall not marry a prostitute or a woman who has been defiled, neither shall they marry a woman <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3353F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3353F\"></sup>divorced from her husband, for the priest is holy to his God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You shall sanctify him, for he offers the bread of your God. He shall be holy to you, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3354G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3354G\"></sup>I, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who sanctify you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3354H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3354H\"></sup>am holy.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the daughter of any priest, if she profanes herself by whoring, profanes her father; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3355I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3355I\"></sup>she shall be burned with fire.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3356J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3356J\"></sup>“The priest who is chief among his brothers, on whose head the anointing oil is poured and who has been consecrated to wear the garments, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3356K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3356K\"></sup>shall not let the hair of his head hang loose nor tear his clothes.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He shall not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3357L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3357L\"></sup>go in to any dead bodies nor make himself unclean, even for his father or for his mother.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3358M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3358M\"></sup>He shall not go out of the sanctuary, lest he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3358N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3358N\"></sup>profane the sanctuary of his God, for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3358O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3358O\"></sup>consecration of the anointing oil of his God is on him: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And he shall take a wife in her virginity.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>A widow, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3360P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3360P\"></sup>or a divorced woman, or a woman who has been defiled, or a prostitute, these he shall not marry. But he shall take as his wife a virgin of his own people,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>that he may not profane his offspring among his people, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3361Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3361Q\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who sanctifies him.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Speak to Aaron, saying, None of your offspring throughout their generations who has a blemish may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3363R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3363R\"></sup>approach to offer the bread of his God.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For no one who has a blemish shall draw near, a man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3364S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3364S\"></sup>blind or lame, or one who has a mutilated face <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3364T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3364T\"></sup>or a limb too long,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>or a man who has an injured foot or an injured hand,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>or a hunchback or a dwarf or a man with a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3366U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3366U\"></sup>defect in his sight or an itching disease or scabs or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3366V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3366V\"></sup>crushed testicles.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>No man of the offspring of Aaron the priest who has a blemish shall come near to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3367W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3367W\"></sup>offer the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s food offerings; since he has a blemish, he shall not come near to offer the bread of his God.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He may eat the bread of his God, both of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3368X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3368X\"></sup>the most holy and of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3368Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3368Y\"></sup>holy things,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>but he shall not go through the veil or approach the altar, because he has a blemish, that he may not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3369Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3369Z\"></sup>profane my sanctuaries, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3369AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3369AA\"></sup>for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who sanctifies them.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So Moses spoke to Aaron and to his sons and to all the people of Israel."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to Aaron and his sons so that they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3372A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3372A\"></sup>abstain from the holy things of the people of Israel, which they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3372B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3372B\"></sup>dedicate to me, so that they do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3372C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3372C\"></sup>profane my holy name: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Say to them, ‘If any one of all your offspring throughout your generations approaches the holy things that the people of Israel dedicate to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3373D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3373D\"></sup>he has an uncleanness, that person shall be cut off from my presence: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>None of the offspring of Aaron who has a leprous disease or a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3374E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3374E\"></sup>discharge may eat of the holy things <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3374F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3374F\"></sup>until he is clean. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3374G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3374G\"></sup>Whoever touches anything that is unclean through contact with the dead or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3374H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3374H\"></sup>a man who has had an emission of semen,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3375I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3375I\"></sup>whoever touches a swarming thing by which he may be made unclean or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3375J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3375J\"></sup>a person from whom he may take uncleanness, whatever his uncleanness may be—",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>the person who touches such a thing shall be unclean until the evening and shall not eat of the holy things unless he has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3376K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3376K\"></sup>bathed his body in water.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the sun goes down he shall be clean, and afterward he may eat of the holy things, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3377L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3377L\"></sup>they are his food.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3378M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3378M\"></sup>He shall not eat what dies of itself or is torn by beasts, and so make himself unclean by it: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They shall therefore keep my charge, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3379N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3379N\"></sup>lest they bear sin for it and die thereby when they profane it: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3379O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3379O\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who sanctifies them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3380P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3380P\"></sup>“A lay person shall not eat of a holy thing; no foreign guest of the priest or hired worker shall eat of a holy thing,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>but if a priest buys a slave as his property for money, the slave may eat of it, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3381Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3381Q\"></sup>anyone born in his house may eat of his food.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>If a priest's daughter marries a layman, she shall not eat of the contribution of the holy things.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But if a priest's daughter is widowed or divorced and has no child and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3383R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3383R\"></sup>returns to her father's house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3383S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3383S\"></sup>as in her youth, she may eat of her father's food; yet no lay person shall eat of it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3384T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3384T\"></sup>And if anyone eats of a holy thing unintentionally, he shall add <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3384U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3384U\"></sup>the fifth of its value to it and give the holy thing to the priest.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3385V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3385V\"></sup>shall not profane the holy things of the people of Israel, which they contribute to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and so cause them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3386W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3386W\"></sup>to bear iniquity and guilt, by eating their holy things: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3386X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3386X\"></sup>for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who sanctifies them.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Speak to Aaron and his sons and all the people of Israel and say to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3388Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3388Y\"></sup>When any one of the house of Israel or of the sojourners in Israel presents a burnt offering as his offering, for any of their vows or freewill offerings that they offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>if it is to be accepted for you it shall be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3389Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3389Z\"></sup>male without blemish, of the bulls or the sheep or the goats.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3390AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3390AA\"></sup>You shall not offer anything that has a blemish, for it will not be acceptable for you.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And when anyone <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3391AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3391AB\"></sup>offers a sacrifice of peace offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3391AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3391AC\"></sup>to fulfill a vow or as a freewill offering from the herd or from the flock, to be accepted it must be perfect; there shall be no blemish in it.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Animals <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3392AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3392AD\"></sup>blind or disabled or mutilated or having a discharge or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3392AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3392AE\"></sup>an itch or scabs you shall not offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> or give them to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as a food <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3392AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3392AF\"></sup>offering on the altar.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You may present a bull or a lamb that has a part <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3393AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3393AG\"></sup>too long or too short for a freewill offering, but for a vow offering it cannot be accepted.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Any animal that has its testicles bruised or crushed or torn or cut you shall not offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; you shall not do it within your land,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>neither shall you offer as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3395AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3395AH\"></sup>the bread of your God any such animals gotten from a foreigner. Since there is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3395AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3395AI\"></sup>blemish in them, because of their mutilation, they will not be accepted for you.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3397AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3397AJ\"></sup>“When an ox or sheep or goat is born, it shall remain seven days with its mother, and from the eighth day on it shall be acceptable as a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But you shall not kill an ox or a sheep <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3398AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3398AK\"></sup>and her young in one day.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And when you sacrifice a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3399AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3399AL\"></sup>sacrifice of thanksgiving to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you shall sacrifice it so that you may be accepted.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>It shall be eaten on the same day; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3400AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3400AM\"></sup>you shall leave none of it until morning: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3401AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3401AN\"></sup>“So you shall keep my commandments and do them: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3402AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3402AO\"></sup>And you shall not profane my holy name, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3402AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3402AP\"></sup>I may be sanctified among the people of Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3402AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3402AQ\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who sanctifies you,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>who brought you out of the land of Egypt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3403AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3403AR\"></sup>to be your God: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel and say to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3405A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3405A\"></sup>These are the appointed feasts of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3405B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3405B\"></sup>proclaim as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3405C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3405C\"></sup>holy convocations; they are my appointed feasts.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3406D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3406D\"></sup>“Six days shall work be done, but on the seventh day is a Sabbath of solemn rest, a holy convocation. You shall do no work. It is a Sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in all your dwelling places.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3407E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3407E\"></sup>“These are the appointed feasts of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3407F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3407F\"></sup>holy convocations, which you shall proclaim at the time appointed for them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3408G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3408G\"></sup>In the first month, on the fourteenth day of the month at twilight, is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s Passover.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And on the fifteenth day of the same month is the Feast of Unleavened Bread to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; for seven days you shall eat unleavened bread.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3410H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3410H\"></sup>On the first day you shall have a holy convocation; you shall not do any ordinary work.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But you shall present a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for seven days. On the seventh day is a holy convocation; you shall not do any ordinary work.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel and say to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3413I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3413I\"></sup>When you come into the land that I give you and reap its harvest, you shall bring the sheaf of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3413J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3413J\"></sup>the firstfruits of your harvest to the priest,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3414K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3414K\"></sup>wave the sheaf before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, so that you may be accepted. On the day after the Sabbath the priest shall wave it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And on the day when you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3415L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3415L\"></sup>wave the sheaf, you shall offer a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3415M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3415M\"></sup>male lamb a year old without blemish as a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3416N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3416N\"></sup>And the grain offering with it shall be two tenths of an ephah of fine flour mixed with oil, a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with a pleasing aroma, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3416O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3416O\"></sup>and the drink offering with it shall be of wine, a fourth of a hin.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And you shall eat neither bread nor grain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3417P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3417P\"></sup>parched or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3417Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3417Q\"></sup>fresh until this same day, until you have brought the offering of your God: it is a statute forever throughout your generations in all your dwellings.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3418R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3418R\"></sup>“You shall count seven full weeks from the day after the Sabbath, from the day that you brought the sheaf of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3418S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3418S\"></sup>wave offering.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You shall count <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3419T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3419T\"></sup>fifty days to the day after the seventh Sabbath. Then you shall present a grain offering of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3419U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3419U\"></sup>new grain to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You shall bring from your dwelling places two loaves of bread to be waved, made of two tenths of an ephah. They shall be of fine flour, and they shall be baked with leaven, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3420V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3420V\"></sup>firstfruits to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And you shall present with the bread seven lambs a year old without blemish, and one bull from the herd and two rams. They shall be a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with their grain offering and their drink offerings, a food offering with a pleasing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And you shall offer one <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3422W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3422W\"></sup>male goat for a sin offering, and two male lambs a year old as a sacrifice of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3422X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3422X\"></sup>peace offerings.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the priest shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3423Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3423Y\"></sup>wave them with the bread of the firstfruits as a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with the two lambs. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3423Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3423Z\"></sup>They shall be holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the priest.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And you shall make a proclamation on the same day. You shall hold a holy convocation. You shall not do any ordinary work. It is a statute forever in all your dwelling places throughout your generations.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3425AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3425AA\"></sup>when you reap the harvest of your land, you shall not reap your field right up to its edge, nor shall you gather the gleanings after your harvest. You shall leave them for the poor and for the sojourner: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel, saying, In <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3427AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3427AB\"></sup>the seventh month, on the first day of the month, you shall observe a day of solemn rest, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3427AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3427AC\"></sup>a memorial proclaimed with blast of trumpets, a holy convocation.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You shall not do any ordinary work, and you shall present a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3430AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3430AD\"></sup>on the tenth day of this seventh month is the Day of Atonement. It shall be for you a time of holy convocation, and you shall afflict yourselves and present a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And you shall not do any work on that very day, for it is a Day of Atonement, to make atonement for you before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>For whoever is not afflicted on that very day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3432AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3432AE\"></sup>shall be cut off from his people.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And whoever does any work on that very day, that person I will destroy from among his people.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>You shall not do any work. It is a statute forever throughout your generations in all your dwelling places.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>It shall be to you a Sabbath of solemn rest, and you shall afflict yourselves. On the ninth day of the month beginning at evening, from evening to evening shall you keep your Sabbath.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3437AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3437AF\"></sup>On the fifteenth day of this seventh month and for seven days is the Feast of Booths to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>On the first day shall be a holy convocation; you shall not do any ordinary work.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>For seven days you shall present food offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3439AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3439AG\"></sup>On the eighth day you shall hold a holy convocation and present a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. It is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3439AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3439AH\"></sup>solemn assembly; you shall not do any ordinary work.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3440AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3440AI\"></sup>“These are the appointed feasts of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which you shall proclaim as times of holy convocation, for presenting to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> food offerings, burnt offerings and grain offerings, sacrifices and drink offerings, each on its proper day,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3441AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3441AJ\"></sup>besides the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s Sabbaths and besides your gifts and besides all your vow offerings and besides all your freewill offerings, which you give to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“On the fifteenth day of the seventh month, when you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3442AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3442AK\"></sup>gathered in the produce of the land, you shall celebrate the feast of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> seven days. On the first day shall be a solemn rest, and on the eighth day shall be a solemn rest.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3443AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3443AL\"></sup>you shall take on the first day the fruit of splendid trees, branches of palm trees and boughs of leafy trees and willows of the brook, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3443AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3443AM\"></sup>you shall rejoice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God seven days.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3444AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3444AN\"></sup>You shall celebrate it as a feast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for seven days in the year. It is a statute forever throughout your generations; you shall celebrate it in the seventh month.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3445AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3445AO\"></sup>You shall dwell in booths for seven days. All native Israelites shall dwell in booths,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3446AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3446AP\"></sup>your generations may know that I made the people of Israel dwell in booths when I brought them out of the land of Egypt: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Thus Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3447AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3447AQ\"></sup>declared to the people of Israel the appointed feasts of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3448A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3448A\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Command the people of Israel to bring you pure oil from beaten olives for the lamp, that a light may be kept burning regularly.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Outside the veil of the testimony, in the tent of meeting, Aaron shall arrange it from evening to morning before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> regularly. It shall be a statute forever throughout your generations.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He shall arrange the lamps on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3451B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3451B\"></sup>lampstand of pure gold before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> regularly.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“You shall take fine flour and bake twelve <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3452C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3452C\"></sup>loaves from it; two tenths of an ephah shall be in each loaf.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And you shall set them in two piles, six in a pile, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3453D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3453D\"></sup>on the table of pure gold before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And you shall put pure frankincense on each pile, that it may go with the bread as a memorial portion as a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3455E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3455E\"></sup>Every Sabbath day Aaron shall arrange it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> regularly; it is from the people of Israel as a covenant forever.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3456F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3456F\"></sup>it shall be for Aaron and his sons, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3456G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3456G\"></sup>they shall eat it in a holy place, since it is for him a most holy portion out of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s food offerings, a perpetual due.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now an Israelite woman's son, whose father was an Egyptian, went out among the people of Israel. And the Israelite woman's son and a man of Israel fought in the camp,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and the Israelite woman's son <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3458H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3458H\"></sup>blasphemed the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3458I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3458I\"></sup>Name, and cursed. Then they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3458J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3458J\"></sup>brought him to Moses. His mother's name was Shelomith, the daughter of Dibri, of the tribe of Dan.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3459K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3459K\"></sup>they put him in custody, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3459L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3459L\"></sup>till the will of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> should be clear to them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3461M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3461M\"></sup>“Bring out of the camp the one who cursed, and let all who heard him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3461N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3461N\"></sup>lay their hands on his head, and let all the congregation stone him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And speak to the people of Israel, saying, Whoever curses his God shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3462O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3462O\"></sup>bear his sin.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Whoever <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3463P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3463P\"></sup>blasphemes the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall surely be put to death. All the congregation shall stone him. The sojourner as well as the native, when he blasphemes the Name, shall be put to death.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3464Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3464Q\"></sup>“Whoever takes a human life shall surely be put to death.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3465R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3465R\"></sup>Whoever takes an animal's life shall make it good, life for life.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>If anyone injures his neighbor, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3466S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3466S\"></sup>as he has done it shall be done to him,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>fracture for fracture, eye for eye, tooth for tooth; whatever injury he has given a person shall be given to him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3468T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3468T\"></sup>Whoever kills an animal shall make it good, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3468U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3468U\"></sup>and whoever kills a person shall be put to death.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You shall have the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3469V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3469V\"></sup>same rule for the sojourner and for the native, for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So Moses spoke to the people of Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3470W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3470W\"></sup>they brought out of the camp the one who had cursed and stoned him with stones. Thus the people of Israel did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3471A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3471A\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses on Mount Sinai, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel and say to them, When you come into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3472B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3472B\"></sup>the land that I give you, the land shall keep a Sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For six years you shall sow your field, and for six years you shall prune your vineyard and gather in its fruits,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>but in the seventh year there shall be a Sabbath of solemn rest for the land, a Sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. You shall not sow your field or prune your vineyard.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3475C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3475C\"></sup>You shall not reap what grows of itself in your harvest, or gather the grapes of your undressed vine. It shall be a year of solemn rest for the land.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The Sabbath of the land shall provide food for you, for yourself and for your male and female slaves and for your hired worker and the sojourner who lives with you,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and for your cattle and for the wild animals that are in your land: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3477D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3477D\"></sup>all its yield shall be for food.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“You shall count seven weeks of years, seven times seven years, so that the time of the seven weeks of years shall give you forty-nine years.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then you shall sound <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3479E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3479E\"></sup>the loud trumpet on the tenth day of the seventh month. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3479F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3479F\"></sup>On the Day of Atonement you shall sound the trumpet throughout all your land.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And you shall consecrate the fiftieth year, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3480G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3480G\"></sup>proclaim liberty throughout the land to all its inhabitants. It shall be a jubilee for you, when each of you shall return to his property and each of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3480H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3480H\"></sup>you shall return to his clan.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>That fiftieth year shall be a jubilee for you; in it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3481I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3481I\"></sup>you shall neither sow nor reap <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3481J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3481J\"></sup>what grows of itself nor gather the grapes from the undressed vines.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For it is a jubilee. It shall be holy to you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3482K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3482K\"></sup>You may eat the produce of the field.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3483L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3483L\"></sup>“In this year of jubilee each of you shall return to his property.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And if you make a sale to your neighbor or buy from your neighbor, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3484M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3484M\"></sup>you shall not wrong one another.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3485N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3485N\"></sup>You shall pay your neighbor according to the number of years after the jubilee, and he shall sell to you according to the number of years for crops.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>If the years are many, you shall increase the price, and if the years are few, you shall reduce the price, for it is the number of the crops that he is selling to you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3487O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3487O\"></sup>You shall not wrong one another, but you shall fear your God, for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3488P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3488P\"></sup>“Therefore you shall do my statutes and keep my rules and perform them, and then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3488Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3488Q\"></sup>you will dwell in the land securely.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3489R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3489R\"></sup>The land will yield its fruit, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3489S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3489S\"></sup>you will eat your fill <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3489T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3489T\"></sup>and dwell in it securely.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And if you say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3490U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3490U\"></sup>‘What shall we eat in the seventh year, if <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3490V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3490V\"></sup>we may not sow or gather in our crop?’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3491W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3491W\"></sup>command my blessing on you in the sixth year, so that it will produce a crop sufficient for three years.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3492X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3492X\"></sup>When you sow in the eighth year, you will be eating some of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3492Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3492Y\"></sup>the old crop; you shall eat the old until the ninth year, when its crop arrives.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“The land shall not be sold in perpetuity, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3493Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3493Z\"></sup>the land is mine. For you are strangers and sojourners with me.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And in all the country you possess, you shall allow a redemption of the land.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“If your brother becomes poor and sells part of his property, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3495AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3495AA\"></sup>then his nearest redeemer shall come and redeem what his brother has sold.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>If a man has no one to redeem it and then himself becomes prosperous and finds sufficient means to redeem it,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>let <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3497AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3497AB\"></sup>him calculate the years since he sold it and pay back the balance to the man to whom he sold it, and then return to his property.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But if he does not have sufficient means to recover it, then what he sold shall remain in the hand of the buyer until the year of jubilee. In the jubilee it shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3498AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3498AC\"></sup>be released, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3498AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3498AD\"></sup>he shall return to his property.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“If a man sells a dwelling house in a walled city, he may redeem it within a year of its sale. For a full year he shall have the right of redemption.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>If it is not redeemed within a full year, then the house in the walled city shall belong in perpetuity to the buyer, throughout his generations; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3500AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3500AE\"></sup>it shall not be released in the jubilee.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But the houses of the villages that have no wall around them shall be classified with the fields of the land. They may be redeemed, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3501AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3501AF\"></sup>they shall be released in the jubilee.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>As for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3502AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3502AG\"></sup>the cities of the Levites, the Levites may redeem at any time the houses in the cities they possess.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And if one of the Levites exercises his right of redemption, then the house that was sold in a city they possess shall be released in the jubilee. For the houses in the cities of the Levites are their possession among the people of Israel.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But the fields <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3504AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3504AH\"></sup>of pastureland belonging to their cities may not be sold, for that is their possession forever.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“If your brother becomes poor and cannot maintain himself with you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3505AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3505AI\"></sup>you shall support him as though he were a stranger and a sojourner, and he shall live with you.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3506AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3506AJ\"></sup>Take no interest from him or profit, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3506AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3506AK\"></sup>fear your God, that your brother may live beside you.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3507AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3507AL\"></sup>You shall not lend him your money at interest, nor give him your food for profit.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3508AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3508AM\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt to give you the land of Canaan, and to be your God.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3509AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3509AN\"></sup>“If your brother becomes poor beside you and sells himself to you, you shall not make him serve as a slave:",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>he shall be with you as a hired worker and as a sojourner. He shall serve with you until the year of the jubilee.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3511AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3511AO\"></sup>Then he shall go out from you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3511AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3511AP\"></sup>he and his children with him, and go back to his own clan and return <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3511AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3511AQ\"></sup>to the possession of his fathers.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>For they are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3512AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3512AR\"></sup>my servants, whom I brought out of the land of Egypt; they shall not be sold as slaves.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3513AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3513AS\"></sup>You shall not rule over him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3513AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3513AT\"></sup>ruthlessly but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3513AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3513AU\"></sup>shall fear your God.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>As for your male and female slaves whom you may have: you may buy male and female slaves from among the nations that are around you.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3515AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3515AV\"></sup>You may also buy from among the strangers who sojourn with you and their clans that are with you, who have been born in your land, and they may be your property.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>You may bequeath them to your sons after you to inherit as a possession forever. You may make slaves of them, but over your brothers the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3516AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3516AW\"></sup>you shall not rule, one over another ruthlessly.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“If a stranger or sojourner with you becomes rich, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3517AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3517AX\"></sup>your brother beside him becomes poor and sells himself to the stranger or sojourner with you or to a member of the stranger's clan,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>then after he is sold he may be redeemed. One of his brothers may redeem him,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>or his uncle or his cousin may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3519AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3519AY\"></sup>redeem him, or a close relative from his clan may redeem him. Or if he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3519AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3519AZ\"></sup>grows rich he may redeem himself.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>He shall calculate with his buyer from the year when he sold himself to him until the year of jubilee, and the price of his sale shall vary with the number of years. The time he was with his owner shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3520BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3520BA\"></sup>rated as the time of a hired worker.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>If there are still many years left, he shall pay proportionately for his redemption some of his sale price.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>If there remain but a few years until the year of jubilee, he shall calculate and pay for his redemption in proportion to his years of service.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>He shall treat him as a worker hired year by year. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3523BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3523BB\"></sup>He shall not rule ruthlessly over him in your sight.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>And if he is not redeemed by these means, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3524BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3524BC\"></sup>he and his children with him shall be released in the year of jubilee.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>For it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3525BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3525BD\"></sup>to me that the people of Israel are servants. They are my servants whom I brought out of the land of Egypt: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>“You shall not make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3526A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3526A\"></sup>idols for yourselves or erect an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3526B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3526B\"></sup>image or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3526C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3526C\"></sup>pillar, and you shall not set up a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3526D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3526D\"></sup>figured stone in your land to bow down to it, for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3527E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3527E\"></sup>You shall keep my Sabbaths and reverence my sanctuary: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3528F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3528F\"></sup>“If you walk in my statutes and observe my commandments and do them,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3529G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3529G\"></sup>I will give you your rains in their season, and the land shall yield its increase, and the trees of the field shall yield their fruit.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3530H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3530H\"></sup>Your threshing shall last to the time of the grape harvest, and the grape harvest shall last to the time for sowing. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3530I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3530I\"></sup>you shall eat your bread to the full and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3530J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3530J\"></sup>dwell in your land securely.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3531K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3531K\"></sup>I will give peace in the land, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3531L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3531L\"></sup>you shall lie down, and none shall make you afraid. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3531M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3531M\"></sup>I will remove harmful beasts from the land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3531N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3531N\"></sup>and the sword shall not go through your land.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You shall chase your enemies, and they shall fall before you by the sword.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3533O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3533O\"></sup>Five of you shall chase a hundred, and a hundred of you shall chase ten thousand, and your enemies shall fall before you by the sword.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3534P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3534P\"></sup>I will turn to you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3534Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3534Q\"></sup>make you fruitful and multiply you and will confirm my covenant with you.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall eat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3535R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3535R\"></sup>old store long kept, and you shall clear out the old to make way for the new.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3536S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3536S\"></sup>I will make my dwelling among you, and my soul shall not abhor you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3537T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3537T\"></sup>And I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3537U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3537U\"></sup>will walk among you and will be your God, and you shall be my people.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3538V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3538V\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, that you should not be their slaves. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3538W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3538W\"></sup>And I have broken the bars of your yoke and made you walk erect.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3539X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3539X\"></sup>“But if you will not listen to me and will not do all these commandments,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>if you spurn my statutes, and if your soul abhors my rules, so that you will not do all my commandments, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3540Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3540Y\"></sup>break my covenant,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>then I will do this to you: I will visit you with panic, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3541Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3541Z\"></sup>wasting disease and fever that consume the eyes and make the heart ache. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3541AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3541AA\"></sup>you shall sow your seed in vain, for your enemies shall eat it.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3542AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3542AB\"></sup>set my face against you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3542AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3542AC\"></sup>you shall be struck down before your enemies. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3542AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3542AD\"></sup>Those who hate you shall rule over you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3542AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3542AE\"></sup>you shall flee when none pursues you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And if in spite of this you will not listen to me, then I will discipline you again <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3543AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3543AF\"></sup>sevenfold for your sins,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and I will break <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3544AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3544AG\"></sup>the pride of your power, and I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3544AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3544AH\"></sup>will make your heavens like iron and your earth like bronze.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3545AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3545AI\"></sup>your strength shall be spent in vain, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3545AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3545AJ\"></sup>your land shall not yield its increase, and the trees of the land shall not yield their fruit.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3546AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3546AK\"></sup>“Then if you walk contrary to me and will not listen to me, I will continue striking you, sevenfold for your sins.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3547AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3547AL\"></sup>I will let loose the wild beasts against you, which shall bereave you of your children and destroy your livestock and make you few in number, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3547AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3547AM\"></sup>your roads shall be deserted.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3548AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3548AN\"></sup>if by this discipline you are not turned to me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3548AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3548AO\"></sup>but walk contrary to me,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3549AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3549AP\"></sup>then I also will walk contrary to you, and I myself will strike you sevenfold for your sins.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3550AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3550AQ\"></sup>I will bring a sword upon you, that shall execute vengeance for the covenant. And if you gather within your cities, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3550AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3550AR\"></sup>I will send pestilence among you, and you shall be delivered into the hand of the enemy.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3551AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3551AS\"></sup>When I break your supply of bread, ten women shall bake your bread in a single oven and shall dole out your bread again by weight, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3551AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3551AT\"></sup>you shall eat and not be satisfied.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3552AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3552AU\"></sup>if in spite of this you will not listen to me, but walk contrary to me,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>then I will walk contrary to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3553AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3553AV\"></sup>in fury, and I myself will discipline you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3553AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3553AW\"></sup>sevenfold for your sins.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3554AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3554AX\"></sup>You shall eat the flesh of your sons, and you shall eat the flesh of your daughters.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3555AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3555AY\"></sup>I will destroy your high places and cut down your incense altars and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3555AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3555AZ\"></sup>cast your dead bodies upon the dead bodies of your idols, and my soul will abhor you.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3556BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3556BA\"></sup>lay your cities waste and will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3556BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3556BB\"></sup>make your sanctuaries desolate, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3556BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3556BC\"></sup>I will not smell your pleasing aromas.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3557BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3557BD\"></sup>I myself will devastate the land, so that your enemies who settle in it shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3557BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3557BE\"></sup>appalled at it.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3558BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3558BF\"></sup>I will scatter you among the nations, and I will unsheathe the sword after you, and your land shall be a desolation, and your cities shall be a waste.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3559BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3559BG\"></sup>“Then the land shall enjoy its Sabbaths as long as it lies desolate, while you are in your enemies' land; then the land shall rest, and enjoy its Sabbaths.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>As long as it lies desolate it shall have rest, the rest that it did not have on your Sabbaths when you were dwelling in it.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And as for those of you who are left, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3561BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3561BH\"></sup>I will send faintness into their hearts in the lands of their enemies. The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3561BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3561BI\"></sup>sound of a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3561BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3561BJ\"></sup>driven leaf shall put them to flight, and they shall flee as one flees from the sword, and they shall fall when none pursues.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>They shall stumble over one another, as if to escape a sword, though none pursues. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3562BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3562BK\"></sup>you shall have no power to stand before your enemies.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And you shall perish among the nations, and the land of your enemies shall eat you up.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And those of you who are left shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3564BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3564BL\"></sup>rot away in your enemies' lands because of their iniquity, and also because of the iniquities of their fathers they shall rot away like them.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“But if <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3565BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3565BM\"></sup>they confess their iniquity and the iniquity of their fathers in their treachery that they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3565BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3565BN\"></sup>committed against me, and also in walking contrary to me,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>so that I walked contrary to them and brought them into the land of their enemies—if then their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3566BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3566BO\"></sup>uncircumcised heart is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3566BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3566BP\"></sup>humbled and they make amends for their iniquity,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>then I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3567BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3567BQ\"></sup>remember my covenant with Jacob, and I will remember my covenant with Isaac and my covenant with Abraham, and I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3567BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3567BR\"></sup>remember the land.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3568BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3568BS\"></sup>the land shall be abandoned by them and enjoy its Sabbaths while it lies desolate without them, and they shall make amends for their iniquity, because they spurned my rules and their soul abhorred my statutes.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Yet for all that, when they are in the land of their enemies, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3569BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3569BT\"></sup>I will not spurn them, neither will I abhor them so as to destroy them utterly and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3569BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3569BU\"></sup>break my covenant with them, for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>But I will for their sake remember the covenant with their forefathers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3570BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3570BV\"></sup>whom I brought out of the land of Egypt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3570BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3570BW\"></sup>in the sight of the nations, that I might be their God: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3571BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3571BX\"></sup>These are the statutes and rules and laws that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made between himself and the people of Israel through Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3571BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3571BY\"></sup>on Mount Sinai."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the people of Israel and say to them, If anyone <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3573A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3573A\"></sup>makes a special vow to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> involving the valuation of persons,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>then the valuation of a male from twenty years old up to sixty years old shall be fifty shekels of silver, according to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3574B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3574B\"></sup>shekel of the sanctuary.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If the person is a female, the valuation shall be thirty shekels.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>If the person is from five years old up to twenty years old, the valuation shall be for a male twenty shekels, and for a female ten shekels.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>If the person is from a month old up to five years old, the valuation shall be for a male five shekels of silver, and for a female the valuation shall be three shekels of silver.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And if the person is sixty years old or over, then the valuation for a male shall be fifteen shekels, and for a female ten shekels.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And if someone is too poor to pay the valuation, then he shall be made to stand before the priest, and the priest shall value him; the priest shall value him according to what the vower can afford.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“If the vow is an animal that may be offered as an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all of it that he gives to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is holy.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3581C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3581C\"></sup>He shall not exchange it or make a substitute for it, good for bad, or bad for good; and if he does in fact substitute one animal for another, then both it and the substitute shall be holy.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And if it is any unclean animal that may not be offered as an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, then he shall stand the animal before the priest,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and the priest shall value it as either good or bad; as the priest values it, so it shall be.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3584D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3584D\"></sup>But if he wishes to redeem it, he shall add a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3584E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3584E\"></sup>fifth to the valuation.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“When a man dedicates his house as a holy gift to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the priest shall value it as either good or bad; as the priest values it, so it shall stand.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3586F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3586F\"></sup>And if the donor wishes to redeem his house, he shall add a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3586G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3586G\"></sup>fifth to the valuation price, and it shall be his.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“If a man dedicates to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> part of the land that is his possession, then the valuation shall be in proportion to its seed. A homer of barley seed shall be valued at fifty shekels of silver.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>If he dedicates his field from the year of jubilee, the valuation shall stand,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>but if he dedicates his field after the jubilee, then the priest shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3589H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3589H\"></sup>calculate the price according to the years that remain until the year of jubilee, and a deduction shall be made from the valuation.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3590I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3590I\"></sup>And if he who dedicates the field wishes to redeem it, then he shall add a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3590J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3590J\"></sup>fifth to its valuation price, and it shall remain his.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But if he does not wish to redeem the field, or if he has sold the field to another man, it shall not be redeemed anymore.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But the field, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3592K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3592K\"></sup>when it is released in the jubilee, shall be a holy gift to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, like a field that has been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3592L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3592L\"></sup>devoted. The priest shall be in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3592M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3592M\"></sup>possession of it.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>If he dedicates to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> a field that he has bought, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3593N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3593N\"></sup>which is not a part of his possession,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3594O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3594O\"></sup>then the priest shall calculate the amount of the valuation for it up to the year of jubilee, and the man shall give the valuation on that day as a holy gift to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3595P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3595P\"></sup>In the year of jubilee the field shall return to him from whom it was bought, to whom the land belongs as a possession.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Every valuation shall be according to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3596Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3596Q\"></sup>the shekel of the sanctuary: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3596R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3596R\"></sup>twenty gerahs shall make a shekel.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“But a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3597S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3597S\"></sup>firstborn of animals, which as a firstborn belongs to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, no man may dedicate; whether ox or sheep, it is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And if it is an unclean animal, then he shall buy it back at the valuation, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3598T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3598T\"></sup>and add a fifth to it; or, if it is not redeemed, it shall be sold at the valuation.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3599U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3599U\"></sup>no devoted thing that a man devotes to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, of anything that he has, whether man or beast, or of his inherited field, shall be sold or redeemed; every devoted thing is most holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3600V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3600V\"></sup>No one devoted, who is to be devoted for destruction from mankind, shall be ransomed; he shall surely be put to death.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3601W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3601W\"></sup>“Every tithe of the land, whether of the seed of the land or of the fruit of the trees, is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s; it is holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>If a man wishes to redeem some of his tithe, he shall add a fifth to it.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And every tithe of herds and flocks, every tenth animal of all that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3603X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3603X\"></sup>pass under the herdsman's staff, shall be holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>One shall not differentiate between good or bad, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3604Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3604Y\"></sup>neither shall he make a substitute for it; and if he does substitute for it, then both it and the substitute shall be holy; it shall not be redeemed.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3605Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3605Z\"></sup>These are the commandments that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses for the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3605AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3605AA\"></sup>on Mount Sinai."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;